Sprinkle on cheese and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: cracked wheat bread
directions: Soak cracked wheat in cold water overnight.
Mix together the milk, shortening, salt and molasses.
Add soaked cracked wheat. Dissolve yeast in the warm water; add to other ingredients.
Add half the flour and beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 10 minutes.
Grease dough; cover and let rise until double in size.
Divide into 2 loaves.
Let rise again. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Saute bread in butter until lightly browned.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole. Top with crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Good with ham salad.

title: delicious corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put margarine in baking dish and place in oven to melt.
Meanwhile, mix all ingredients, stirring well. Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until set and golden brown.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in water over low heat.
When melted, remove from heat and add lime gelatin.
After gelatin has dissolved, place mixture in refrigerator long enough to cool, but not set. Whip mixture until large bubbles disappear.
Add remaining ingredients, folding in Cool Whip.
Congeal in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook rosamarina in boiling water 5 to 8 minutes; drain.
In a large bowl, combine rosemarina, chicken, celery, onion and eggs. Save 2 eggs for garnish.
In a small bowl, combine Miracle Whip, lemon juice, salt, white pepper and poultry seasoning.
Fold into chicken mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 16 (1 cup servings)

title: easy mexican noodles
directions: Brown and cook the ground turkey.
Add the salsa and corn to meat mixture.
Stir in the cooked noodles and simmer until hot. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: fruit salad and dressing
directions: Mix and serve on bed of lettuce.
Top with dressing.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix 1st five ingredients together and spread mixture on a plate.
Pour desired amount of sauce or salsa over mixture. Sprinkle drained and deboned crab meat over top.
Use crackers of your choice to scoop up spread.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Add thawed strawberries, diced bananas and pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture into container (mold or glass dish).
Place in refrigerator to jell. Leave remaining gelatin mixture at room temperature.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter.
Add white and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sunday dinner steaks
directions: Dredge steak in flour and pepper.
Brown lightly on both sides in oil.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over top.
Cover with mushrooms and liquid.
Add a layer of sliced onions.
Pour can of gravy that has been mixed with water over the top.
Do not stir.

title: museli morning bread or muffins
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, oil, eggs and almond extract.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix together flour, Museli cereal mixture, baking powder and salt.
Now pour the liquid ingredients into the dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Or spoon into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot potato salad(dutch recipe)
directions: Peel, boil and then slice potatoes.
Dice and fry bacon.
Add flour to bacon and mix.
Add vinegar, sugar and water to the flour and bacon.
Bring to a boil and add to the potatoes which have been mixed with the onion and celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Garnish with parsley.

title: fudge mud slide
directions: Place brownie in a large bowl.
Add ice cream and top with hot fudge sauce and crushed cookie.
Add whipped cream and drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Sprinkle with almonds and top with a cherry.

title: turkey dip
directions: Chop egg very fine and mix with mayonnaise.
Add ginger, crushed garlic, onion and celery, minced very fine.
Add curry powder, salt, lemon and turkey.
Add white wine, if desired, to make a thinner dip.

title: low-fat ice cream sandwiches
directions: Spread Cool Whip over 1 graham cracker sheet.
Top with another graham cracker sheet.
Place on flat plate or pan.
Freeze overnight.

title: pasta with garlic
directions: In a large pot of boiling salt water, cook the spaghetti until done; drain.
Mince the garlic.
Combine the oil, garlic, anchovy paste, parsley, cayenne and butter into the hot pot.
Return the spaghetti to the pot and toss over low heat until butter has melted.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken with pastry
directions: Place chicken in 3 cups water with onion, celery and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender over medium heat.
When tender, remove chicken from broth and debone.
Cut into large chunks and place in the bottom of a greased, 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: easy pineapple-cheese spread
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts.
With damp fingers, roll mixture into a ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate, uncovered, until ready to serve.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pocketbook rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast into warm water.
Sift together and mix the flour, milk, sugar and salt.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Knead in enough flour to keep dough from sticking to hands.
Pat or roll out and cut with small orange juice can. Dip in melted butter.
Fold into pocketbooks.
Allow to rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen after this step.
When taken from freezer, allow 3 hours to thaw and rise.

title: venison ragout
directions: Place carrots, celery, onions, marjoram, pepper, bay leaf, water, olive oil and salt in a bowl.
Cut meat into 3-inch strips 1-inch thick.
Add to vegetable and spice mixture.
Add more water if meat is not covered.
Refrigerate, covered, for 5 hours. Remove meat; drain vegetables and reserve marinade.
Roll meat in flour and brown in skillet.
Brown vegetables in casserole dish. Boil marinade and bouillon for 1 minute.
Add bouillon, marinade and meat to casserole dish; cover and bake for 2 hours at 325°. Add water if it boils dry.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan by the order given. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Season chicken.
Brown lightly in butter or oil.
Remove from fire and drain.
In a large Dutch oven, make a roux of flour and butter, stirring until rich brown. Add vegetables and stir until soft. Slowly add water, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and seasonings. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add cabbage, celery, green pepper, onion, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender, but still crisp.
Serves 6.

title: holiday nuggets
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, margarine and sugar; blend in vanilla and almond extracts.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with fingers.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until the bottoms are lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.
When cool, sprinkle with mixture of confectioners and colored sugar.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: brenda's spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: southern hot cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add onions, peppers, corn, cheese, oil, milk, pimento and sugar.
Stir in flour and meal.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° to 375° until brown.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: grilled shrimp with marinade sauce
directions: Mix soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, honey, lemon, onion and white wine.
Marinate shrimp for 2 hours.
Thread shrimp and fruit on skewers.
Place on grill.
Baste with marinade sauce and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over 1/2 cup of cooked rice.

title: fruit fantastic
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine ginger ale and ice to make 2 cups.
Add to gelatin; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice.
Chill until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices in 6-cup bowl.
Add enough gelatin to just cover apples.
Repeat layering fruits and gelatin.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown chuck in skillet until crumbly.
Stir in garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sour cream, softened cream cheese, green onions and 1 1/2 cups shredded cheese.
Mix well.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese mixture in 8 x 8 x 2 baking pan or dish until all ingredients are used, ending with cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over top. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: quick mushroom steak with rice
directions: In large skillet, brown steaks (thoroughly cook). In separate bowl, combine soup with water. Add mushrooms. Mix together. Pour over steaks. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: roast beef
directions: Place roast in baking dish; salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Mix soups together (in blender or food processor).
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Cover with foil.
Punch holes.
Bake in 350° oven for 4 to 5 hours.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Hold cupcakes, top side down, in palm of hand; spread Cool Whip mixture on bottom and sides.
Press coconut onto frosting.
Place cupcakes, top side down, on serving platter.
Drizzle with melted chocolate. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Store any leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 24 snowballs.

title: orange-date nut bread
directions: Combine dry mixes.
Blend eggs and water; stir into dry mixes until completely moistened.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool.

title: cheesy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon cheese into 8 x 12-inch baking dish and place in oven until cheese melts (5 minutes).
Heat oil in a skillet.
Brown pork chops with seasoned salt.

title: taco crackers
directions: Mix together and pour over crackers.
Mix well.
Bake in oven at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: praline cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and cover bottom with whole graham crackers, placing them as close together as possible. Bring margarine and brown sugar to a boil; let boil for 2 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add nuts and spread mixture evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut and separate.
Let cool.
Store in tin with tight lid.

title: one bowl holiday fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwavable bowl on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Remove from microwave.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts. Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Flour chicken and brown.
Season with lots of paprika and some salt.
In a pot, put in 1 layer of chicken, topped with a layer of onions.
Put in another layer of chicken with onions on top.
Add 2 cups of water and bouillon cubes.
Cook on low heat about 1 hour.
Check to see if more water is needed.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake batter as directed on package.
Put 1/2 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In a saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with butter and milk.
Pour over hot half-baked cake.
Top with chocolate chips and pecans. Pour rest of batter over caramels; bake at 350° for 20 minutes longer.

title: two-tone chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter with sugars until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, but do not stir in yet.
Sprinkle soda and salt over flour and fold in, so these are well distributed.
Mix thoroughly, then add chips.
Bake about 8 minutes, or until light golden.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° until bubbling hot.
Yield: 4 servings.
Diabetic exchange:
2 meats and 1 bread.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium size mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt. Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Pour batter into square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch).

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cut up fresh broccoli in small pieces or use frozen broccoli. Cook until crisp-tender along with small onion.
Use small amount of water when cooking.
Then add cream of celery soup (do not dilute).
Add milk and heat.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and heat together.
You can thicken with cornstarch or flour, if needed. Season with salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Stir in already beaten eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift dry ingredients. Blend them into the mixture.
Stir in the raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 medium loaf pans.

title: fast chocolate pecan fudge
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla (mixture will be dry).
Stir in evaporated milk. Microwave 30 to 60 seconds or until mixture is hot.
Stir until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into 8-inch pan.
Cover.
Chill until firm in refrigerator.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Will also need heavy duty aluminum foil.

title: chris' chocolate cake
directions: Grease (do not flour) a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients for the cake together, using hand mixer until well blended.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 minutes.

title: country french chicken breasts
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat and brown chicken. Stir in soup mix blended with water and lemon juice. Arrange lemon slices on chicken. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened and chicken is done.
To serve, arrange chicken over rice and spoon sauce over chicken.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve as salad or on rolls or bread.

title: celia's ribs
directions: Have the butcher crack the ribs at 2-inch intervals.
Cut ribs into 2-inch pieces.
Marinate the ribs, best overnight.
Set oven temperature to 350°.
Take ribs out of marinade and roast for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with marinade frequently.
Turn up oven for the last few minutes to crisp the ribs.

title: great grandma amiot's gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and spices.
Add egg and molasses. Stir in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Make into small balls, roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix in bowl; mix well.
Stir in pecans and marshmallows.
Add whipped topping; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Remove meat from cooked chicken and chop it up.
Save broth from cooked chicken and use some of it in the stuffing mix instead of water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
Use only the tender stems and flowerets of broccoli.

title: crescent onion bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease a 9-inch round can or pie pan.
Separate each can of dough into 2 long rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.

title: glazed chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until blended (batter will be thick).
Spread evenly into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 15 minutes.
Pour Chocolate Glaze evenly on cake.

title: barbecups
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion.
Separate dough into biscuits.
Place each biscuit in an ungreased muffin cup, pressing dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 10 to 12.

title: alabama stew
directions: Brown ground beef in bottom of stew pot.
Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces and place on top of ground beef.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Tastes great served with cornbread or crackers.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes, stirring rapidly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, stirring rapidly to prevent sticking to pan.
Pour into buttered dish and refrigerate. Cut into squares before serving.

title: original nilla banana pudding
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Blend in 3 egg yolks and milk. Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, for 10 to 12 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Reserve 10 Nilla wafers for garnish. Spread small amount of custard on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover with layers of 1/3 each of the wafers and sliced bananas. Pour about 1/3 of custard over bananas. Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard to make a total of 3 layers of each, ending with custard. Beat egg whites on high speed of electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff but not dry. Spoon on top of custard, spreading to cover entire surface and sealing well to edges. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned. Cool slightly or refrigerate several hours until chilled. Top with reserved wafers. Makes 12 (2/3 cup) servings. Prep: 30 minutes. Bake: 20 minutes.

title: shrimp ball(scampi palle)
directions: Mash shrimp.
Beat
remaining
ingredients together and mix with shrimp.
Shape into
ball
and roll in parsley flakes or ground nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers or fresh cut up vegetables, if desired.
Makes 1 large ball.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in milk.
Sift flour and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thick. Cut into desired shapes.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and let cool.
Makes 2 dozen medium cookies.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Tip the pan to grease the sides.
Add sugar and molasses.
Stir until well dissolved. Bring this mixture to a boil, stirring slowly and constantly. (Candy is done when a drop dropped into cold water becomes brittle.)
Pour taffy into well-greased platter.
When cool enough to handle, grease hands and pull candy from hand to hand until firm and of a gold color.
Draw into a smooth band or twist into rope.
Cut into short lengths with kitchen shears.
Spread on wax paper to finish cooling.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak with onions in margarine.
Add salt, pepper, soup, water and sour cream.
Mix well and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Cook noodles; drain and mix with meat and sauce.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk, Cool Whip and lemonade together.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend all ingredients. Chill and serve with Melba rounds or crackers.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat the first ten ingredients together, then stir in carrots and coconut.
Spoon into Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for 50 or 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Serves 16.

title: white castle
directions: Mix ingredients; press flat on cookie sheet (will fill the whole cookie sheet).
Prick with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares to fit bun; place pickle on each bun.
Place back on cookie sheet, sprinkle with water and cover with foil.
Store in refrigerator until ready.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes (makes about 40 mini White Castles).
Use small dinner rolls.

title: meatballs - anna b's
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olive oil.
Roll into meatballs.
Brown the meatballs in olive oil, then put in the sauce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and blend well.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip pineapple in blender until foamy.
Pour into saucepan. Add sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and pour into mixture.
Cook until thick.
Let cool, then add Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: the best chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Let cool until lukewarm. Add eggs, sugar and vanilla to chocolate.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Cover and chill overnight.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 18 large cookies!
Yum! Yum!

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and carrots.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to mixture. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Make thin confectioners sugar.
Use orange juice for the liquid and frost while the cookies are warm.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with chips (tortilla) or veggies.
Makes 2 cups.

title: homemade barbecue
directions: Brown the roast in a large frying pan.
Place in 5-quart crock-pot.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours or until done.

title: easy milkshake
directions: Pour milk into shaker.
Add ice cream and pudding.
Shake for at least 1 minute.
Pour drink into glass.

title: recipe for leo's shepherd's pie(serves 4)
directions: Peel, boil and mash the potatoes.
Brown the hamburger (loose).
In a 2-quart casserole dish, put in potatoes (bottom layer), put in loose hamburger (middle layer) and add creamed corn (top layer).
Place in oven preheated to 350°.
Heat until creamed corn starts to bubble (15 to 20 minutes).
While heating, wash potato pan and frying pan.
Eat and enjoy!

title: griddle cakes
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg, add milk, and pour slowly on first mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Add butter, drop by spoonful on a greased hot griddle.
Cook on one side, when puffed and full of bubbles and cooked on the edges, turn and cook other side.
Then spread with butter and maple syrup.

title: diabetic apple muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar substitute and spices into a medium mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and oleo.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients.
Blend only until flour is moistened. Fold in apples and pour batter into 12 non-stick muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: In saucepan mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, lemon juice, water and 1 can blueberries.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick. Add other 3 cups of berries and butter.
Mix well and cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, dash of salt, the coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: chocolate pudding squares
directions: Blend with pastry blender or 2 forks and press into pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: doves or quail
directions: Brown doves or quail in real butter after salting and flouring. Add bouillon cubes, dissolved in water.
Add mushrooms and parsley flakes.
Put game back in and simmer until tender.
Add sherry 10 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.
Don't cook too long.

title: "award winning" snow covered chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with shortening, butter, or margarine.
Beat cake mix, water, oil, and eggs in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes or 299 strokes by hand.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Check with toothpick.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Frost completely.
Add coconut flakes (optional).

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter frozen rolls while still frozen and drop into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle dry ingredients, pecans and raisins.
Drizzle butter on top.
Cover with cloth and let set until morning.
Bake on bottom rack at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Debone chicken in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add diced onion and Velveeta cheese.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle on the chicken mixture.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel.
Pour over the ingredients already in dish.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: skinny blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow 2-quart casserole. Fork blend the biscuit mix and skim milk.
Spoon on top of blueberry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wild rice
directions: Cook wild rice 5 minutes, then drain.
Cook both rices together for 15 minutes; drain.
Saute celery and onion in butter. Place rice in baking dish, adding celery, onion, cheese and water chestnuts.
Add one cup of milk.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: scot's and mike's skillet trout
directions: Into pie plate, pour milk.
On waxed paper, place flour.
Dip fish in milk, then in flour to coat.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, get oil hot.
Cook fish, turning carefully with pancake turner once, for 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Place on warm plate.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Chop.
Roll chicken into each crescent roll.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Melt cheese and soup in smaller boiler; pour over crescents.
Place in preheated oven, uncovered, at 350° until brown.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Saute oleo, chopped celery, onion and green pepper.
Mix soups, chicken broth, Tabasco, olives, salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce, pimentos and chili powder.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Grate American cheese.
Mix and bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
After it cooks, sprinkle some cheese on top and let melt.
Can divide and put in freezer.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out both loaves of dough.
Place 1 loaf on a cookie sheet.
Layer ingredients in any order.
Top with other loaf of dough.
Seal all the way around.
Vent the top of dough to let steam escape.
Bake at 300° to 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crescent roll casserole
directions: Boil chicken and dice into small pieces.
Unfold one crescent roll.
Put a layer of chicken on roll and then a layer of cheese. Place second crescent on top of first and pinch together. Continue this with other crescents.
You will end up with 4 of these.
Lay these 4 filled crescents on a large baking dish. Next, heat cream of chicken soup, 1/2 cup milk and remaining cheese until cheese melts.
Pour this mixture over rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart Pyrex dish.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High until light brown (8 to 10 minutes), stirring once or twice.
Remove from microwave.
Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy. Quickly spread on greased baking sheet.
Quickly spread out as thin as possible for a brittle candy.
Break into pieces.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions (9-inch pie pan).

title: apple delicious
directions: Cut off top of each apple.
(Save to use as a lid.)
Carve out core and a little bit of apple with a spoon.
Mix raisins, spices and nuts in a bowl.
Fill the hole in each apple with raisin mixture.
Put top back on each apple.
Bake the apples in an ovenproof dish at 375° until apples are done.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.

Cook until mixture boils, continue cooking, stirring constantly, until a hard ball forms when dropped in very cold water or 260° on a candy thermometer. Remove from heat and quickly blend in butter or oleo. Pour slowly over popped corn in a large bowl, mixing well. Shape into balls using as little pressure as possible. Butter hands, if necessary.
Mixture will be very hot.
Keep a bowl of cold water for dipping hands to cool.
Makes 14 medium balls.

title: shrimp with curry
directions: Combine the shrimp, undiluted soup, onion dip, curry powder and cayenne pepper in a skillet and mix well. Cook until heated through. Serve over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 11 x 7 baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add juice from noodles if too dry.
Bake at 400° until bubbles in center.

title: no cook strawberry jam
directions: Slice and crush 1 pint strawberries.
Drain pineapple and reserve 3/4 cup juice.
Add pineapple and 4 cups sugar to strawberries.
Set 10 minutes.
Stir pineapple juice into one box Sure-Jell; heat and boil 1 minute.
Stir into pineapple, strawberry mixture.
Stir 3 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil; cool until lukewarm. Sift salt, soda and baking powder into plain flour; do not sift flour before measuring.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.

Add yeast mixture to liquid mixture. Mix in flour. Let stand 2 hours. Knead on floured board; roll dough to 1/4-inch thick (or thinner). Cut with biscuit cutter. Make mark across each roll with knife; roll in melted margarine (I use Parkay).
Place in pan, leaving space for each to rise.
Let rise until at least double in size. Bake at 400° to 425°, depending on oven, until brown.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients and set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Wash peppers and pack tightly in hot jars.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to about 300°.
Grease cookie trays in advance. Beat 2 egg whites until semi-stiff.
Slowly add 3/4 cup sugar while continuing to beat.
When egg whites and sugar are stiff, add a small package of chocolate bits or nuts, etc.
Place by small spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Place in oven.
Turn off heat.
Take out when hardened.

title: admonition coconut cake
directions: The night before baking the cake, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Store in refrigerator in a covered bowl.
Next day, prepare cake and bake.
Turn out layers and cool.
Split each layer to a total of 4 layers.
Fill and frost with sour cream mixture.
Store in the refrigerator in cake box.
Do not cut for 4 days.

title: sweet and sour pot roast
directions: Sprinkle flour on sirloin tip with salt and pepper.
Brown the sirloin tip in the fat, add onions and bay leaf.
Combine water and wine vinegar, cinnamon, brown sugar and vermouth.
Cook covered, (low heat) 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water if necessary.
Turn meat, cook until tender about 30 minutes.
Add 4 to 6 crumbled gingersnaps, cook until sauce thickens.

title: pierogie casserole
directions: Saute onions and butter. Cook noodles as directed and cool. Prepare mashed potatoes and add some cheese to the potatoes. On bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan, place a layer of onion and butter, a layer of noodles, then potatoes, then onions and cheese. Repeat layers 3 or 4 times. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Egg noodles may be substituted for lasagna noodles.)

title: coconut fingers
directions: Cut and quarter each slice into 4 pieces. Dip strips into condensed milk. Cover all sides and roll in coconut. Place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until delicately brown. Cookies become crisp when cool. (Ground or cut up nuts may be added to coconut.)

title: new england barbecue chicken
directions: Brown
chicken in small amount of oil.	Brown the onion and then simmer with all remaining ingredients for 30 minutes. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Put in 1/2 c. M&Ms. drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops of cookies with 1 cup M&Ms. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttery bread pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix 3/4 cup water with the sugar and salt.
Add yeast mixture.
Stir once and add flour.
Stir until dough begins to stick; add melted butter.
Mix well.
Knead on board 2 minutes.
Rest dough (covered) for 15 minutes.
Divide and roll pretzel shape.
Place on greased sheets. Beat egg yolk with 2 tablespoons water.
Brush each pretzel. Sprinkle with salt (optional).
Let rise 30 minutes.
Should double in size.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Rotate pans to ensure even browning.
Serve warm.
Makes 24 (3-inch) pretzels.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients.
Firm up in refrigerator.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: lucky if there's any left cake
directions: Mix flour, margarine and finely chopped pecans together and spread like a graham cracker crust in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Cool completely.

title: make a dream pie
directions: Combine whipped topping mix, 1 cup milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high with electric mixer, about 6 minutes or until thick enough to form peaks.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix.
Blend on low; beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil; mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon and allspice.
Fold in zucchini and nuts.
Grease two loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown meats.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil and then simmer for about 30 minutes.
For more juice add water.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Mix eggs, peanut butter, vanilla, salt and soda.
Add flour and oats.
Spread dough in slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 to 24 minutes at 350°. While hot, cover with milk chocolate pieces and allow to melt before icing.

title: sherry chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Brown chicken in olive oil.
Remove chicken and brown onion until clear.
Add sherry, bouillon and chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken liver and rice dish
directions: Cut liver into small pieces.
Saute onion in margarine in saucepan.
Add liver and brown.
Put rice, liver and onion and stock (or water) into a casserole dish.
Mix together with dash of salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve.

title: linguini with roasted tomatoes and garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

Combine cherry tomatoes, 1 tablespoon oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and garlic in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; toss gently. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes, or until garlic is browned, stirring occasionally.
(Tomato skins will pop.)
Squeeze the garlic cloves to extract the pulp; discard skins.
Mash the garlic pulp. Add this mashed pulp to the tomato mixture, stirring gently.
Combine tomato mixture, 1 tablespoon oil, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pasta, parsley and basil in a large bowl; toss gently. Yield:
Four 1-cup servings.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups (or 1/2) of the measured flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquid until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in remaining 3 cups of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) bread pans (greased and sprinkled with cornmeal).
Sprinkle top with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan and cool.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn out on wire rack.

title: copy solution(make prints from comics)
directions: Will need a small dish, 2 spoons, bright colored comics, scissors, white paper and extra newspaper.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Combine salt, cottage cheese and sour cream in blender.
Blend and pour over potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle American cheese on top and bake in 2 quart casserole for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, and seasonings.
Add soup, water and noodles and place in 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle cheese around edges of casserole and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. 4-6 Servings.

title: crab bisque(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Saute onions and crabmeat in butter.
Add soups and blend. Add sherry, milk and a lot of parsley.
Serve hot.

title: burger mix burgers
directions: Grind the beans, nuts, seeds and oats in the blender to consistency of coarse flour.
For best results, process only 1/2 cup at a time.
Combine mixture with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in a covered container at cool room temperature or refrigerate.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Pinch off pieces of cake and place in a large bowl, making a layer.
Cut up strawberries and layer on cake. Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream and powdered sugar.
Put a layer of this over the berries.
Repeat layers using all ingredients.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Drain blueberries.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add to juice. Cook until thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add butter and lemon juice. Add berries.
Cool.
Cut 1/2 banana into small pieces and add to berry mixture.
Line baked pie crust, sides and bottom with rounds of bananas.
Pour cooled mixture over crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chiffon layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, beat egg whites with 1/3 cup sugar until thick and glossy but not stiff.
Set aside. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add milk, oil, vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Scrape bowl frequently.
Fold or stir egg whites into batter until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 to 20 minutes before removing from pans.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook and drain sausage; set aside.
Separate dough and make pizza on greased 12-inch pan.
Press and seal.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough and sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine eggs, milk, oregano, and peppers and pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a large kettle or saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs; beat well.
Stir together the flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Form balls; roll in sugar (granulated) and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Recipe may be halved.

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Cook and drain package of chopped broccoli.
Brown the celery and onion in 1/3 cup butter.
Add to this mixture the broccoli, mushrooms and garlic cheese. Serve with chips.

title: egg drop soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring water and bouillon cubes to a boil. Meantime, make a paste with flour and water.
Add to boiling mixture, stirring constantly.
Gradually add beaten egg to boiling mixture, stirring constantly and continue to boil 1 to 2 minutes until egg is done.
Remove from heat and season with pepper, Worcestershire sauce or teriyaki sauce, if desired.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream the cheese and butter. Add flour.
Make in balls and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fudge meltaways
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter
and
square
chocolate in small saucepan.
Blend sugar,
teaspoon vanilla, eggs, crumbs and coconut into butter and chocolate mixture.
Mix well and press into ungreased baking dish, 11
x
1/2 x 1 1/2-inches. Refrigerate.

title: summer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into serving size pieces into salad bowl.
Add Mandarin oranges, pecans and salad dressing.
Toss lightly.

title: corn and potato chowder(yields 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Combine bacon and onion in a 4-quart casserole.
Cook on High for 9 to 11 minutes or until bacon is cooked and onion is tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Drain.

title: fried turkey seasoning
directions: Rub turkey with seasoning inside and out (baste generously). Let turkey baste overnight in refrigerator. Fry at 250 for 5 minutes per pound. Do not cover pot.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Sprite.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 or 2 hours ahead of serving time.
Serve when slushy. Add Sprite just before serving.
Serves 35.

title: how to cook a turkey breast
directions: Wash and remove rib case (optional).
Sprinkle with lemon pepper, salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place in large Corning dish with a cup of water.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Cut heat off and leave dish in oven until oven cools. Turkey is ready to slice and serve.
Roast or ham may be cooked the same way.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel rind and remove all pink.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Soak 3 hours in salt and water.
Rinse and drain and cook in enough water to cover until just tender.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar, water, lemon and cinnamon.
Add rind and simmer until it looks clear. Pack in hot, sterile jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 quarts.

title: turkey cobb salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Individually prepare 4 salad plates.
Line plates with lettuce. Distribute turkey, tomatoes and avocado on plates.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Top with sour cream, green onions and olives.
Serve with salsa.

title: lit'l link wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap dough and separate along perforations.
Cut each piece into 3 sections.
Cut each section into 3 lengthwise pieces.
Braid the dough and then wrap around meat and bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 250°
oven for 4 hours.
Bake in covered casserole.

title: double apple salad
directions: Sprinkle diced apples with citric powder.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Season meat with salt and brown in hot oil in large skillet. Add soy sauce, garlic and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes until meat is tender. Add green pepper, onions and celery. Cover. Simmer 10 minutes. Add tomatoes.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling water.
Mash until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; beat until light and fluffy.
Cool. Cover and place in refrigerator.
Use anytime within 2 weeks.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon and remove from pan.
Brown onion in bacon grease and remove from grease.
Add all ingredients and mix.
Put in casserole dish and cook at 350° until bubbling.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix dates, candy, coconut and nuts with 1/4 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour with baking soda and salt.
Fold sifted dry ingredients into creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in fruit and nut mixture.
Spoon batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cornbread stuffing with the melted butter or oleo.
Put half of the mixture in baking pan.
Put the carrot and onion in a blender, or chop very fine.
Mix the vegetables with the soup, a little salt and pepper, squash and sour cream.
Pour over the first mixture and top with the remaining cornbread stuffing mix. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix together and roll into 1-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.

title: golden salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with rotary eggbeater until light and fluffy.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Drain tuna.
Cook peas and carrots. In large bowl, mix soup and milk.
Add tuna, noodles and vegetables.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and put a few pieces of butter on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: pork chops with apple rings
directions: Use apples that are unpeeled, cored and sliced into rings. Brown chops on both sides.
Place apple rings in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with margarine. Place pork chops on top of apples.
Cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 3 g, fat 16 g, calories 288.

title: kuchen
directions: Use apples, peaches, plums, blueberries or mix blueberries and peaches for the fruit.

title: pound cake
directions: Place ingredients in large bowl and beat for 3 minutes.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 325° for one hour until done.
Use loaf pan or tube pan.

title: cranberry wine salad
directions: Pour water over Jell-O. Add cranberry sauce while hot and stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and wine. Cool to jelling point and fold in nuts. Refrigerate until set. Serve with or without dressing.

title: liver fricassee
directions: Pour boiling water over liver; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain, wipe dry and cut into strips.
Dredge with the next 3 ingredients. Brown quickly in hot bacon fat (or other).
Add rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Thicken with a little flour. Serve with cooked noodles.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Spread small jar of Marshmallow Creme over cooled cake.

title: easy spinach soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt 2 1/2 Tbsp. butter.
Add the carrots, scallions and clove of gallic; saute until the scallions are soft. Bring the chicken broth to a boil, stir in rice or pasta.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Just before serving, stir the spinach into the hot liquid.
Cook for two to three minutes until spinach is done.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with parmesan cheese and/or croutons if desired.

title: speedy baked beans with wieners
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in skillet until crisp; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: taylor's spicy pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl except pretzels.
Stir in broken beer pretzels.
Spread out on baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours; stir often.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add horseradish and ketchup to taste.
Serve with crackers or carrots and celery sticks.

title: oatmeal hermits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening and sugars until creamy. Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together. Add alternately with milk to creamy mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oven cashew chicken salad
directions: Mix in order given except for 1/2 of onion rings and paprika. Bake in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole (covered) for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onion rings and paprika and bake an additional 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: delight and leeman's soup
directions: In a frying pan, with the oil, cook the stew meat.
When it's done put the meat and the drippings in a pot; add the can of soup and one can of water.
Add all of the other ingredients.
On medium heat, cook until potatoes and carrots are done.
Serves 4.

title: crab ala king
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour with margarine.
Slowly add milk. Cook until thickened to make white sauce.
Add all other ingredients.
Keep hot over double boiler.
Serve over crisp toast, biscuits, patty shells or rice.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: In cake pan, mix fudge brownie mix, cherries, marshmallows and walnuts.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Remove; let cool for 15 minutes on rack.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and butter.
Add eggs and beat with mixer about 2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet, combine sugar, cream and butter; set control at 280°.
Bring mixture to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off.
Beat.
Stir marshmallows and peanut butter in until melted and blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: marinated beef kabobs
directions: Mix wine, oil, garlic, thyme and pepper in large plastic bag, then add meat.
Push out air, tie bag securely and turn gently to coat meat.
Store in bowl; marinate at room temperature for 1 hour (in refrigerator if longer).
Arrange meat cubes about 1/2 inch apart on skewers.
Broil in preheated broiler about 3 to 4 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes for rare to medium-rare, or until of desired doneness, turning once.
Serves 8.

title: reuben dip on rye party rounds
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat and serve hot on rye party rounds.

title: grandma's chocolate fudge
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan combine butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir for 1 minute until marshmallows melt completely.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels.
Add margarine in top of double boiler. Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over mixture.
Pour the other half of batter over all. Bake another 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown beef. Pour off any accumulated grease. Add celery, green pepper and onion; saute. Add tomatoes and their juice. Add remaining ingredients, except for the Cheddar cheese. Simmer 20 minutes. Pour into 9 x 12 casserole. Spread Cheddar cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in top of double boiler. Add 2 cups water. Combine egg yolks with juice and beat.
Add to rest of mixture.
Cook until thick over boiling water for 25 minutes. (This does away with starchy taste.) Now add lemon extract, butter and vinegar. Stir thoroughly.
Pour into deep 9-inch pie shell and let cool.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: In a 9 x 13 dish place a layer of graham crackers.
Mix instant pudding by box directions.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour half on layer of crackers, another layer of crackers ending with filling.
In sauce pot mix cocoa, milk & sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Then stir in margarine & vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Let it get cold, then spread over filling.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Just before serving, place sherbet in punch bowl. Add ginger ale and soda; stir until sherbet is almost dissolved.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; put in a 7 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle over the remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix together the ground beef, sausage, onion, parsley and crumbs.
Beat egg with spices; add to meat mixture.
Mix well. Shape into meatballs.
You can make them whatever size you prefer. Usually 1-inch size meatballs work best! Brown meatballs in the oil; drain on paper towel.
Add flour to oil that has meat residue in it.
It makes it taste better!!!
Brown flour until you get a light brown paste.
Add can of soup and broth to make a gravy. Add your meatballs; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; keep warm.
Makes about 60 meatballs.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and roll in pecans.

title: joey's bean dip
directions: In medium saucepan, bring Hormel chili to a boil, then add onion, comino, chili powder and garlic salt.
Stir well.
Add hot sauce.
Bring to a boil again, then add cream cheese (to make it thicker).
Turn heat off; add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir well. Good with tortilla chips.
Enjoy.

title: anna's fudge
directions: Melt margarine, pour over sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Add cocoa.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix together.
Place into square pan.
Cut into small pieces.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix 3/4 cup self-rising cornmeal and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexicorn salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together. Taste to see if you need to add any salt. Add salt if needed.

title: beth harris's slimming quiche(this is quick, easy, good hot or cold, and dietetic too.)
directions: *Note:
Add to spinach juice enough water to make 1 cup and blend in 1/3 cup dry milk powder, if desired.

title: pumpkin bar
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased jelly roll pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: summer vegetable salad with basil marinade
directions: Whisk together orange juice, basil, shallots, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add tomatoes, zucchini and corn; toss to combine.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours, tossing occasionally.
Remove from refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: stuffing lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in a large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add 1 cup of sauce and water; bring to a boil. Add stuffing mix; stir just to moisten.
Remove from heat.

title: cheese and salsa dip
directions: Add onions and green pepper if desired.

title: indiana lemon angel pie
directions: 1. Meringue Shell:
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar in a medium size bowl until foamy white.
Beat in the one cup of sugar in Tbsp. at a time, until the meringue forms stiff white glossy peaks.
Lightly butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Spoon meringue over bottom and up sides to form a shell.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Put nuts and syrup in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut biscuits and put on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are light brown.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Mix pork and beans.
Heat until bubbly.
This is great served with corn bread.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: In a boiler, bring to a boil sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cool.
Add to drained vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator for several hours.
Keeps well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix in baking dish.

title: summer sandstorm
directions: Pour ingredients in glass; fill glass with milk and top with nutmeg.

title: potato chowder
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine potatoes, onion, carrot, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and bouillon cubes.
Add enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not drain.
Scald milk by heating to 180° or until tiny bubbles form around the edges of pan.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of milk and add butter and flour to hot milk, stirring with wire whisk.
Add remaining 4 1/2 cups hot milk to undrained vegetables. Then stir thickened hot milk mixture.
Stir until blended.
Simmer 15 minutes on low.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salted peanut crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt butter.
Brush on rosemary, thyme, basil and garlic. Bake in 250° oven until dry.

title: bean and sausage soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine juice cocktail, undrained beans, potatoes and sausage.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender and mixture is heated through.
Sprinkle each serving with some of the cheese.
Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: hungarian meatballs
directions: Combine ground chuck, garlic salt, parsley, seasonings, milk, egg and crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into small meatballs.
Heat oil and add Kitchen Bouquet.
Brown meatballs in oil mixture. Remove meatballs and stir in flour.
Add mushrooms and sour cream; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter,
1 cup flour and powdered sugar, thoroughly and put in 8 x	8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix eggs, lemon juice, lemon rind, sugar, flour and baking powder. Spread over crust.
Bake
at
for
25 minutes.
Cool and dust with confectioners
sugar.
Can	be
doubled
and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, syrup and water in saucepan. Stir and cook until mixture thickens (about 5 minutes).
Add gelatin and blend well.
Cool.
Put berries into cooled baked crust.
Spoon gelatin mixture and over berries.
Chill thoroughly.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Lightly brown meat (be sure it's well done); drain real well. I cook hamburger meat first, then my sausage.

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain. Heat milk and soup until smooth.
Put hamburger and potatoes in casserole.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: river potatoes
directions: Line large pan with foil.
Layer, starting with potatoes, then bacon, sliced onion and sliced pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour with oleo, then add milk, baking powder and salt. Mix thoroughly and turn onto floured surface.
Roll quite thin and pat on melted oleo.
Mix raisins, cinnamon and sugar.
Spread on dough and roll up like a jellyroll.
Cut into slices 1-inch thick and arrange in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: honey custard
directions: Combine eggs, salt and honey.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour in custard cups; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups in pan of hot water and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until set.
(If desired, instead of using custard cups, pour into a large mold and bake as above for 45 minutes.)

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
(Do not overmix.)
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes (or until done).

title: lazy-way quiche
directions: Toast bread, cut into cubes and arrange in bottom of small casserole.
Arrange tomatoes on top of bread cubes.
Sprinkle cheese over tomatoes.
Mix in small bowl milk, egg, mustard, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread, cheese and tomatoes.
Bake in preheated oven 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses; add sauce and let stand several hours in refrigerator.
Form into two balls; roll in finely chopped nuts or parsley.
Paprika, also, may be sprinkled on.

title: blueberry torte (or cherry)
directions: Gradually add 2 cups sugar to egg whites.
Fold in nuts and saltines and bake in 13 x 9-inch buttered pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: beau monde vegetable dip
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Combine water, diced potatoes and beef powder in a 3-quart pot.
Simmer until potatoes are very tender.
Mash potatoes but do not drain.
Add pepper, Beau Monde and cumin.
Simmer 10 minutes. Blend flour into Pet milk and stir slowly into soup.
Blend sour cream into soup.
Heat just to boiling.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: turketti
directions: Boil pasta in salty water until barely tender; drain.
Saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese, then add sauteed vegetables and spaghetti.
Pour into large casserole sprayed with Pam. Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until contents are bubbly and top is brown, about 25 minutes.
With French bread and a green salad, this recipe serves a large group.
We always made Turketti to take to the beach during spring break.

title: spinach stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops from tomatoes; remove pulp, leaving shells intact. Reserve pulp for other uses.
Sprinkle inside shells with salt; invert to drain.

title: beer batter
directions: This batter is used as a coating when deep frying chicken, fish or any vegetable.

title: frosty banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to boil.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Combine juices; stir in sugar syrup.
Add bananas, which have been crushed and mashed in a blender.
Freezer until of a thick, mushy consistency.
Spoon mushy mixture into punch bowl. Mix in club soda.
Serve immediately.
Makes 50 (4-ounce) servings.

title: walking sandwich
directions: For each sandwich, fill between slices of rye with Swiss cheese, 2 slices of corned beef and Summer Slaw.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: amaretto mousse
directions: Heat sugar in water until dissolved.
Set aside.
Mix eggs, salt and chocolate in blender.
Add sugar mixture slowly.
Blend until thickened.
Cool.
Add Amaretto. fold in 3/4 of whipped cream.
Pour into small wine glasses.
Chill 4 hours.
Before serving, spoon a dollop of whipped cream on each serving.

title: farmer's corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn, sour cream, milk, butter, egg and Jiffy mix.
Pour into a baking dish coated with Pam non-stick spray. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Melt shortening in large skillet. Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Cook chicken in shortening over medium heat, 15 to 20 minutes, or until light brown.
Remove chicken; set aside.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: e-z potato salad
directions: Mix together well the salad dressing, mayonnaise and sugar. Blend in the onion, celery and parsley.
Mix into the potatoes; salt and pepper to taste.
(You may wish to add a couple of hard-boiled eggs stirred into the salad; be my guest.)

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Spread half the cookie crumbs in an 11-inch dish.
Cream margarine, confectioners sugar and cream cheese into mixer bowl until smooth.
Combine pudding mix, milk and whipped topping in large bowl; mix well.
Spread in prepared dish; top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with gummy worms.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: turkey-noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Arrange 1/2 of mixture in a buttered, shallow, 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Add remaining turkey-noodle mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well; batter will be slightly lumpy.
Pour on hot griddle. Cook on each side until done. Serve warm with butter and warm maple syrup.

title: skillet macaroni and hamburger
directions: Brown beef and onion in shortening; drain excess fat.
Stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni and mix well.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix with mayonnaise and salt to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and cover with soups.
Place in casserole dish.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Place cornbread crumbs into a large bowl; pour in hot chicken broth.
Cover and let set for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients in given order.
Pour mixture into a large greased baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: cheese stuffing
directions: Mix together and stuff celery.
This is one lunch protein.

title: chocolate cake(very rich)
directions: Beat together eggs, sour cream, water and oil until thoroughly mixed.
Add cake mix and instant chocolate pudding.
Beat until smooth and stir in package of chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with chocolate or vanilla icing.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together (except chocolate and paraffin).
Roll into balls.
Stick toothpicks into the balls. Dip balls into chocolate paraffin mixture.

title: crock-pot chicken(easy and low fat)
directions: Wash and dry chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with Tony's and put in crock-pot.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours.
Do not add any liquid.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli in bottom of greased casserole.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine egg, soups, mayonnaise and juice in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Spread cheese on top.
Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add egg.
Mix sour milk and baking soda.
Add to sugar-margarine-egg mixture along with flour and vanilla.
Mix in rhubarb.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with sugar five minutes before removing from oven.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix
flour,
white
sugar,
Wesson oil, brown sugar and salt. Take out 1 cup mixture to crumble on top of cake.
Then add
egg, buttermilk,
soda,
pecans and vanilla to the first mixture.
Mix well
and pour in greased and floured pan.
Then sprinkle the 1 cup
of
mixture
you took out before on top of the cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; add margarine.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix dark brown sugar, white sugar, soda, cinnamon, eggs, plain flour and nutmeg together.
Stir into the oatmeal mixture.
Blend these together well.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: chicken spectacular casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly greased a 2-quart casserole (shallow) baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish until well blended.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: quick mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet and press centers to form small bowl shape.
Add 1 teaspoon Ragu to each biscuit.
Cube cheese and place one cube on each biscuit. Bake 10 minutes or until brown.

title: marie's cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugars, egg and milk. Add cream of tartar, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Add flour and mix in well. Stir in oatmeal, corn flakes, coconut and nuts. Roll in balls and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 balls (small).
Can leave out cheese, if desired.

title: cheese ring
directions: Shred cheeses.
Combine first five ingredients and mix well. Sprinkle about 1/4 cup chopped nuts into oiled seven cup ring mold.
Press cheese mixture into mold.
Sprinkle remaining pecans. Chill until firm, 4 or 5 hours.

title: dieter's strawberry dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth or beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Use as a basic fruit dip.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until served.

title: southern punch pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add unbeaten eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and crushed pineapple.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to first mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: low-sodium spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in olive oil in a large saucepan.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: ice cream(electric or hand crank machine)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, flour, vanilla, 1/2 can milk and 1 cup of water (bring to a scald). When thickened, strain and cool (chill remaining milk). When ready to freeze, add rest of milk, water and chocolate; stir well. Enjoy.

title: buffet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add pineapple with juice. Chill until slightly thick. Mix rest of ingredients and fold into congealed Jell-O. Mold in pan or muffin pans. Serves 12.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer slowly 1 hour or more, depending on how much time you have.
Cook spaghetti separately.
Drain when spaghetti is tender.
Serve meat sauce over spaghetti.

title: texas fudge
directions: Grate cheese, put 1/2 in bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish. Cover with chilies. Top with other half of cheese. Mix eggs with Worcestershire, pour over cheese and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let cool until it falls out of dish.

title: marinade steak(great for venison)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl or a marinater.
Lay meat in and let soak 24 hours.
If using marinater, turn over a couple of times in the 24 hours.
If using bowl, just mix meat so all the meat gets soaked.
You don't have to fry this meat long.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small pan and boil for 3 minutes. With steel blade in place, add cream to the mixing container of food processor.
Process until very thick whipping cream forms, about 1 minute.
Transfer to 2-quart mold.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs or grated cheese halfway through baking.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, total cooking time.

title: john's brown cake
directions: In large bowl, mix flour and sugar together; set aside.
In a saucepan, mix butter, water, and cocoa; bring to a rapid boil. Pour mixture over flour and sugar; mix by hand; add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, cinnamon, and vanilla.
Mix well; pour in well greased 11x16x1-1/2 pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: bringhurst pecan cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating
well.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating mixture well after
each addition.
Combine 3 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and nutmeg;
add to creamed mixture alternately with bourbon, beginning and ending
with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Dredge raisins
and
pecans
in
remaining
1/4 cup flour;
stir into batter.
Spoon batter into a heavily greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at
for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool
cake
in
pan
for
minutes. Remove cake from pan and let cool completely.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put oysters in a dish with water and boil 6 to 8 minutes. Salt and pepper.
Add milk and heat.
Add butter.
Serve hot.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix together soup, water, onion, Cheez Whiz, rice and melted butter.
Add broccoli to the other ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, noodles, soup, salt, pepper and milk in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Crumble potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until chips are brown.

title: fat free mountain frosting
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in medium or small saucepan.
Bring to boiling quickly.
Boil rapidly; don't stir.
Boil until temperature is 242° or until 6 to 8-inch thread spins when dripped from a spoon.
While mixture boils, beat egg whites to stiff peaks. When boiled mixture reaches proper stage, pour in a thin stream into egg whites, beating on high constantly.
Beat until glossy peaks form.
Put in food coloring.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler with remaining ingredients. After it is all melted and mixed thoroughly, put into 6 to 8 (1/2 pound) oleo tubs or put in fancy dishes and give away as gifts. Super good with crackers or celery sticks!

title: colorado curried tuna dip
directions: Mix and chill, serve with crackers and veggies.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Make sure it isn't too loose. Scoop into muffin tin and bake at 350° approximately 15 to 18 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and curry. Drain and dry fruits and place in large 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add butter mixture. Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: festive chicken supreme
directions: Flour chicken and brown in oil. Mix all ingredients, except asparagus and pour into a shallow 3-quart casserole. Arrange chicken over mixture and pour some of the mixture over the chicken breasts to coat. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Meanwhile, prepare asparagus and cut in half crosswise. Remove casserole from oven and arrange asparagus between the chicken breasts. Cover tightly with foil and bake 30 minutes until chicken is tender an asparagus is tender-crisp.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cooking meatballs on the stove requires constant attention. Instead, arrange uniformly sized meatballs (you can use a small ice cream scoop to measure) in a shallow, greased baking pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, no turning necessary.
Simply add your favorite sauce and continue cooking until done.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: easy pecan rolls(uncooked)
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, confectioners sugar, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Knead until all sugar is thoroughly blended. Shape into 8 rolls.
Wrap each in plastic and freeze.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: favorite elegant butter creams
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese at room temperature.
Add vanilla. Then add 3 cups of flour and mix good.
Roll out on a floured cutting board.
Cut with small cutter and add small amount of filling.
Pinch ends together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: governor's apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch round cake pan. Combine apples, nuts and melted butter in large mixing bowl.
Stir in egg, vanilla and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to apple mixture, stirring only until blended.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until lightly browned and tester comes out clean.
This cake can be served warm, but is even better if made ahead of time wrapped in plastic and refrigerated.
Yields:
8 servings.

title: popover upside-down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, basil, fennel seed and marjoram.
Heat to boiling. Boil 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange Mozzarella cheese slices on top.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, 1 cup flour and the salt with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over cheese slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake until puffy and golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Process well. Let tortillas get soft at room temperature.
Spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll tortillas up tightly.
Line up in 9 x 13-inch casserole, cover tightly and refrigerate overnight or a minimum of 3 hours.
Remove from refrigerator, slice tortillas in 1/2 inch rounds.
Serve with Pace's medium Mexican sauce.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots and raisins.
Moisten with mayonnaise or French dressing.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peaches `n' cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a 10-inch pie pan with cooking spray.
In a medium mixing bowl, add flour, salt and baking powder and stir to combine.
Add melted margarine, milk, egg and pudding mix.
Mix all ingredients on medium speed of an electric mixer.
Pour mixture into prepared pie pan.
Lay peaches over pudding.
In separate bowl, combine cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar and mix on medium speed until well-combined.
Gently spread cream cheese mixture over peaches; leaving 1-inch from edge of pie plate uncovered.
In a small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon sugar with cinnamon.
Mix and sprinkle over pie.
Bake for 35 minutes. Served hot with a dollop of fat-free vanilla ice cream and additional peaches.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Blend in cheeses, onion, beef, olives and Ranch dressing.
Blend all this very good and form a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 3 tablespoons of juice. Combine sugar and flour; stir in pineapple juice. Add cheese and pineapple chunks; mix well. Spoon mixture into 1-quart greased casserole baking dish.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil.
Add flour and sugar.
Cream together with first mixture.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Bake in cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inches) for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Toast English muffins.
Put toasted muffins on a flat pan. Put spoonful of tomato sauce on muffins.
Put 2 slices of cheese on muffins, then put a teensy bit more sauce.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Drizzle with olive oil.
Put pan in oven at 365° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, honey and dry milk.
Roll into quarter size balls, then roll in desired coating.
After coating, place on sheet cake pan lined with wax paper and chill.

title: candied apples
directions: Bring sugar, water and red hots to a boil.
Add cinnamon sticks and food coloring.
