Drop peeled, quartered apples (preferably Jonathan) into boiling liquid.
Cook until tender. Enough syrup for about 10 or 12 apples.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and place in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Mix together shortening, brown sugar and flour.
Cover apples with this mix and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: pork hot dish
directions: Cook pork, celery, pepper and onion in oil until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
In large bowl, combine pork mixture, noodles, soups, corn, milk, salt and pepper; mix well. Put in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until heated through.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray a tube pan lightly with Pam.
Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Place pieces in a covered bowl.
Shake pieces well in sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan. Arrange biscuit pieces on top, placing them in brick fashion.
Melt margarine and brown sugar and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and glaze.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash and cut stems 1/2 inch from okra pod.
Place okra and peppers in hot jars.
Bring vinegar mixture to a boil; pour over okra and seal.
This makes a very crisp and tasty pickle.

title: louisiana cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and cream in large pot (2-quart).
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until (soft ball) 234° to 240° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; let set for 5 minutes.
Add butter; beat for 5 minutes.
Add flour and beat for 15 minutes. Add nuts; pour into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jar.
Pour hot water (boiling) over them and let stand.
While preparing vinegar mixture, put vinegar and water in pot and boil.
Add 1/8 teaspoon alum, clove of garlic and sprig of dill.
Drain off first water and pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: mildred hammond's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually stir in grated Cheddar cheese, pineapple, 1 cup nuts, green pepper, seasoned salt and onions. Chill.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage.
Melt cheese; mix together with Bisquick and shape into balls.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid, jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and pineapple juice.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours until it becomes slush.
Put in punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Serves 20.

title: cottage cheese whip
directions: Add softened Cool Whip to cottage cheese.
Mix in dry jello. Drain fruit well and add to mixture.
Refrigerate to stiffen.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Bring 2 1/2 cups water and salt to a boil in a medium-size saucepan; add rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Keep warm.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned; stir often.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add mushrooms, green onions, green pepper and water chestnuts to skillet.
Saute 5 minutes or until tender.
Dissolve bouillon in 1 1/4 cups water. Combine soy sauce, cornstarch, brown sugar and ginger.
Stir in bouillon mixture; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in cashews.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: chocolate chip cream cookies(very soft moist cookie)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.

Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Add chopped nuts and chips; blend well. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet at once and cool.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: homemade soap
directions: Caution:
When mixing lye and water, follow precautions to prevent injury.
Never mix lye with hot or warm water (always cold water).
Clean rancid fats by boiling in equal amounts of water. Remove from heat.
Chill by adding 1 quart cold water for each gallon.
Remove fat from top.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt margarine in pot. Add next 4 ingredients. Cook until thickened, stirring at same time. Add cut up chicken (boiled). Just before serving, add 2 tablespoons cooking sherry. Serve over rice.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: With mixer, cream the sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients one at a time.
Roll dough in small balls; press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown at edges. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Pare and core apples, saving skins and core and simmer in water.
Drain and reserve liquid from syrup.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; stir only until moistened.
Roll out to size of tea towel; cut into 6 or 8 squares.
Put apples on each square of dough.
Put 1 teaspoon butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon mixture in each apple. Pinch dough together over apple.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 9-inch ungreased baking dish, stir together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Stir together brown sugar and remaining cocoa; smooth over top of mixture in baking dish.
Pour hot water over all ingredients.

title: magic cookie bar
directions: Melt margarine. Mix crumbs together and press into pan, 13 x 9-inch. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 325° to 350° preheated oven (or until lightly browned). Cool thoroughly before cutting into bars.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or a large platter.
Spread bean dip. Spread guacamole.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; spread on top.
Chop tomatoes and spread.
Spread black olives. Spread on onions (tops and bottom).
Spread grated cheese.
Serve with chips.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add salt, pepper, catsup and milk.
Simmer until thick.
Spread on buns.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti in a lot of salted water, al dente.
At the same time saute the pancetta with Parmigiano and a little salt. In another pan melt butter; put eggs whipped.
Drain spaghetti and mix everything.
Let it sit for a couple of minutes, then serve.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt 1 cup butter, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa in microwave. Mix in flour, sugar and salt.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, sour cream and soda.
Mix the two batters together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (even if center doesn't appear done).

title: bernadine davis' potato salad
directions: Boil whole unpeeled potatoes about 1 hour. Test potatoes with a fork to see if they are done.
Pour off hot water.
Let sit in cold water about 20 minutes to cool down.
Peel and cube potatoes into bite size chunks.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix all fruit in a large bowl.
Combine all dry ingredients; sift over fruit mixture.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add to fruit and flour mixture; mix by hand, adding enough orange juice to make right consistency.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place the first 4 ingredients in a blender or food processor and chop finely.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the blender.
Puree until all ingredients are smoothly blended into a sauce.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Blend and pour into pie shell. Chill; top with more Cool Whip.

title: green bean stew
directions: Place meat in pot.
Cover with water; let boil for half an hour, skimming broth.
Wash and cut beans.
Add to meat and cook until meat is tender.
Add onion, tomatoes and spices.
Fry garlic in butter; add to beans.
Cook until beans are tender. Serve with fluffy rice.

title: oougooie
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, 1 egg and pecans (will be crumbly). Spread into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: pork chops l'orange
directions: Season and brown chops on the top of the stove.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Sprinkle rice in pan.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Add chops on top.
Pour chicken stock (well salted) over chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together and dip with nacho chips.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water, pineapple juice, vinegar and salt.
Chill. When slightly thickened, add remaining ingredients.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup; cook over low heat, stir constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and then add eggs, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell and top with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Cut chicken into little pieces.
Brown chicken and put into baking dish.
Pour picante sauce over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Put in a greased oblong 3-quart glass dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 hour.
Continue baking at 325° for 2 to 3 hours until done.
Uncover during last 1/2 hour.

title: cow patties
directions: In a double boiler simmer water. Melt chocolate chips and shortening. Stir until smooth. Remove from heat, stir in rest of ingredients. Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper and chill.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Ritz
crackers.
Melt
margarine;
pour over Ritz cracker crumbs.
Press
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.	Melt
gallon ice cream in a large bowl. Add fresh milk and chocolate pudding; combine thoroughly.
Pour into
cooled
crust and freeze.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Return to freezer.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Set aside 1/3 of the farmer cheese and chiles for garnish. Cover the bottom of a 12 x 7-inch casserole dish with half of the enchilada sauce.
In blender or food processor, combine 2/3 of the farmer cheese and chiles, onion, yogurt, Neufchatel cheese, cottage cheese and hot salsa; blend well.

title: shoo-fly cakes
directions: Mix the flour, brown sugar, butter and salt; save 1 cup for crumbs.
Mix water, Karo and soda together; add to flour mixture. Sprinkle crumbs on top; bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
May also make cupcakes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and cool.
Mix with beans.
Add all other ingredients in large bowl, except Fritos and dressing.
Just before serving, add these and toss.

title: banana cookies
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients. Add oil, egg, bananas, oatmeal, chips and pecans. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: pasta chicken carbonara
directions: Place bacon in 3-quart casserole.
Cover with paper towel and microwave on High 8 to 12 minutes, stirring after 5 minutes, until crisp.
Remove bacon with slotted spoon; drain and reserve.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon in casserole.
Stir onion and garlic into fat in casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave 1 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and microwave 4 to 5 minutes or until heated through. Toss with bacon.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, cube, and boil until tender in salt water. Drain and mash.
Mix bread that has been soaked with eggplant and add eggs, onion, oleo, and seasonings.
Mix well and pour into a greased one-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bubba's bourbon pecan pie
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar, beating until the mixture is fluffy.
Add the eggs gradually, beating after each addition.
Add the corn syrup, salt and bourbon.
Coat the pecans in the flour and add to the mixture.
Pour the filling into the crust and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until the filling is firm.

title: cheese hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, margarine, onion, soup, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan (may butter if you wish). Mix corn flakes and margarine (add garlic to taste, if desired) and spread over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch for a party
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend the water, sugar and bananas until smooth.
Pour into a large container.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice; mix well.
Freeze, stirring occasionally, until slushy.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve. Yield:
About 24 servings.

title: apple or peach coffee cake
directions: In a bowl, mix together butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Cream.
Stir in vanilla. Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet. Arrange sliced fruit on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup raisins or 1 cup nuts or 1 cup raisins.
Bake in 2 (5 x 8-inch) loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 20 minutes on rack before removing from pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs one at a time.
Sift the flour and baking powder.
Add to creamy mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours in oven at 325°.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Sprinkle dates with soda and pour boiling water over all.
Set aside.
Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Gradually stir in walnuts, flour and vanilla.
Combine with date mixture.
Pour into ungreased, paper-lined loaf pan or 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fluffy mustard sauce
directions: Place eggs in a bowl and add sugar, mustard, vinegar, water and salt.
Mix well.

Pour mixture into a double boiler and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Blend in butter and horseradish. Cool thoroughly. Fold in whipped cream. Serve with warm meat.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: company chicken
directions: Melt margarine in roaster.
Add onions and saute until slightly brown.
Sprinkle rice over it.
Lay chicken over rice. Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in baking pan.
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar and milk.
Flour will be lumpy.
Pour over top of peaches and cut pieces of margarine or butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; stir until boiling.
Pour 1/2 sauce in dish.
Add potatoes; add remaining sauce.
Cover; cook 20 minutes in microwave.

title: cheesiest potatoes au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt butter or margarine in shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Add minced garlic. Brush to coat bottom and sides of dish.

title: toffee chip cookies
directions: Mix and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: saucy chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, combine soups, sour cream, broth, onion, mushrooms and seasonings.
Arrange chicken on top of sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Serve chicken and sauce over noodles or rice.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all together for 2 minutes.
Bake in 4 small loaf pans at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hot tuna appetizer
directions: Mix tuna, onion, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce together. Can be stored in refrigerator for a day or two. Put small amount atop a Ritz cracker; top with a square of Cheddar cheese and broil until cheese melts. Serve warm.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in baking dish in oven. Mix cheese, flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake potatoes in bag, coating thoroughly with mixture.
Place potatoes in baking dish in a single layer.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done. Serves 6.

title: microwave caramel fudge
directions: In large, glass bowl, combine sugar, milk and butter. Microwave 2 minutes.
Mix well and microwave 5 minutes, stirring twice during cooking.
Add caramels and microwave 45 to 60 seconds.
Beat until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth. Stir in nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square dish.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: molasses cookies(soft and chewy)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Quick Mix, 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Mix well.
Combine egg yolk and molasses in a small bowl.
Add to dry mixture.
Blend well.
Refrigerate at least one hour.
Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).
Lightly grease baking sheets.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in sugar. Place on prepared baking sheets.
Flatten balls with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until edges are browned.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: ham and chicken dish
directions: Wrap a slice of ham around each breast and place in long casserole dish.
Mix the soup and sour cream together.
Pour over meat and bake at 350° until done (about 35 to 40 minutes).
This is excellent with rice.

title: low calorie beef with peppers and snow peas
directions: In 12-inch no-stick skillet, heat oil.
Add ginger and garlic and saute until garlic is golden.
Add pepper strips, snow peas, mushrooms and green onions and saute until tender-crisp.
Add steak and cook, stirring constantly, until heated through.
Add soy sauce and stir to combine.
Each serving is 342 calories (39 g. protein, 14 g. fat, 16 g. carbohydrate).

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a casserole with lid. Or could use a crock-pot on low setting.
Cook 3 hours at 275°.

title: barbecued spareribs(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except spareribs, in a blender or large, lidded jar, and blend or shake until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Place the ribs in a large, shallow baking pan and cover them with the sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil and marinate at room temperature for several hours.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Leave the foil in place and bake for 45 minutes; uncover and bake another 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve, cut in portions of 2 to 3 ribs.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add flour to mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each ball in sugar mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until cookies begin to fall.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: In covered pan, cook whole potatoes in enough boiling salted water to cover for about 25 minutes, or until almost tender. Drain well.
Peel the warm potatoes.
Quarter and slice potatoes; transfer to mixing bowl.
Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar.
Add the sliced celery, onion, sweet pickle, salt and celery seed to the potatoes; stir the mixture to combine.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing; fold into potato mixture.
Carefully fold in the sliced eggs.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nana's hearty beef stew
directions: Cover bottom of pan with oil.
Shake and coat beef with Durkee brown gravy.
Brown beef in oil.
Add water to cover meat.
Add onion soup mix.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour.
Last 10 minutes add carrots.

title: kapusta
directions: Combine hamburger, eggs, salt, pepper, rice and 1/3 can tomato juice.
Make into meatballs.
Put layer of cabbage, meat and sauerkraut.
Pour rest of juice over it.
Add water.
Bake 1 hour or until cabbage is done.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large frying pan.
Simmer and stir constantly until all liquid has been absorbed.
Spread peanuts onto a greased cookie sheet in a single layer.
Bake in a 250° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: cauliflower and spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, bacon and cauliflower; add mixture of Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, debone and set aside to cool.
Turn oven on to 350°.
Mix together the vegetable soup, salt and pepper to taste.
Put deboned chicken into soup mixture.
Put in oven for about 1 hour.
When hot and bubbly, add biscuits on top and bake until golden brown.
Take out and serve.

title: aunt corrie's heritage pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and flavorings; mix well.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until done, at 300°.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend in butter; stir in chocolate chips and add walnuts if desired.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or ice cream or enjoy as is.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Makes 1 pie.

title: radish relish
directions: Grind radishes, celery and onion.
Put in a large bowl and mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Let stand overnight or at least 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes. Put in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 pints.

title: clams royale
directions: Scrub outside of clam shells thoroughly, discarding any broken or open clams.
Soak clams in salted water for at least 3 hours to clean.
Rinse and drain clams.
Place water in 2-quart casserole. Microwave at High for 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until water boils. Add clams.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 3 to 5 1/2 minutes or until clams open, stirring once.
Remove clams from casserole as they begin to open.
Remove each clam from shell.
Reserve half of each shell.
Mince clams.
Set aside.

title: fluffy hard sauce
directions: Fluffy Hard Sauce:
Cream butter.
Stir in egg yolk. Gradually cream in sugar until fluffy and light.
Add vanilla. Fold in egg whites.
Vary flavor with lemon or orange juice and grated peel or add 1 tablespoon of rum or brandy.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: dr. bird's cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas. Spoon into 3 well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing from pans. Cool completely.
Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots and celery in a large pot. Add water. Cook for 20 minutes or tender. Drain liquid. Set vegetables aside. Saute onion in butter in small pot. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk gradually. Stir gently. Pour into vegetables. Add a cup or more of liquid.

title: sherri's vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.

title: ravioli
directions: Mix together in a bowl the Ricotta cheese, 5 eggs, Romano cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Beat with electric mixer. Set aside.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix flour and butter; mix with other ingredients except pecans.
Butter edges of pie crust; put 1 cup of pecans in each crust.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in each crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: tuna fish luncheon dish
directions: Place mound of tuna salad on English muffin; then slice of pineapple on top of salad.
Top all with Swiss cheese slice. Broil until cheese melts and serve hot!

title: noodles and cheese
directions: Boil water for noodles.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain and put noodles in a bowl.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: In bowl, combine egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and milk and mix well.
Add ground beef and cooked rice and mix well.
Immerse cabbage leaves in boiling water for 3 minutes or just until limp.
Heavy center vein of leaf may be split about 2 1/2-inches.

title: parsley pinwheel loaf
directions: Prepare hot roll mix with one egg and let rise. Beat other egg in a cup. Stir in cheese. Heat remaining ingredients in small saucepan until greens wilt. Cool and blend in beaten egg mix. Punch down dough. Knead a few times. Roll out to an 18 x 6 rectangle. Spread with parsley mix. Roll jelly fashion and place seam side down in greased 9 x 5 x 3 pan. Cover. Let rise again until double in size (about 45 minutes). Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bread gives a hollow sound when tapped.

title: pasta pesto florentine
directions: In food processor, process walnuts and garlic until smooth. Thaw and drain spinach.
Add spinach and all remaining ingredients to walnuts and garlic and process until smooth.
Spoon over choice of cooked pasta.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: funeral dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Heat oven to 350°. Bake until crust forms on top.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine oil, juice, vinegar and salt.
Pour over chicken and toss.
Chill 1 hour and then drain off liquid.
Stir mayonnaise into salad.
Delicious.

title: oven apple butter
directions: In a large covered kettle, simmer the apples and water until tender.
Press through a sieve or food mill.
Measure 1 gallon of pulp; place in a large roaster.
Add sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cinnamon stick.
Cover and bake at 400° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and bake 1 hour longer, stirring occasionally until very thick.
Remove the cinnamon stick.
Pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace.
Adjust the caps. Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yield: 8 pints.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon into a large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla into a large mixer bowl.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Add dry ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done (batter will be very thick).

title: french coconut pies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour, flavor, buttermilk and coconut.
Pour half into each shell and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour on 275°.

title: lemon lush
directions: In 8 x 12-inch dish, mix all together:

title: candied pecans
directions: Cover pecans with water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and drain well.
Mix sugar and spices; set aside.
While pecans are still warm, toss with sugar mixture.
Spread on tray in single layer; let dry, 8 to 24 hours.
Heat oil to 350°.
Fry nuts about 2 minutes, until sugar caramelizes and nuts are dark brown. Drain well.
Sprinkle with salt while still warm if desired. Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs, sugar, vanilla, molasses and oil together. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add nuts.
Put in 4 loaf pans sprayed with Pam and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: mom's huckleberry pudding
directions: Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until tested done and brown.
If using blackberries, do not flour them.
Fold berries into batter.
Eat like cake or in dish with milk on.

title: moo goo ngaw(beef with mushrooms)
directions: *Note:
Canned mushrooms may be used, added at very end of cooking.

title: 44 calorie a cup of salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Ranch Free dressing is also good.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once; stir only until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead gently 1/2 minute.
Pat or roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: sopa de fideos(soup with vermicelli)
directions: Brown fideos in hot oil carefully to avoid breaking coils. Add tomato sauce, broth and seasonings.

title: mrs. rock's surprise cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating with mixer for 3 full minutes after addition of each egg.
Pour into shell and chill for 1 hour.
Cover with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: better than recess cake
directions: Make cake.
While cooling prepare pudding, adding in cream cheese.
Mix into pudding, leaving a little lumpy.
Spread on cake, then drain the pineapple very well and spread over cream cheese.
Spread the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, then serve.

title: vegetable wreath
directions: Cover 10 to 12-inch Styrofoam ring completely with foil. Attach parsley to floral picks.
Insert into ring, covering top and sides completely.
Cut broccoli, cauliflower and green pepper into bite-sized pieces.
Make curls of carrots and celery.
Cut radishes into roses.
Insert wooden toothpick into each vegetable.
Stick vegetables into ring.
Place ring on serving tray.
Place candle or bowl of dip in center of ring.
Yields 20 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: In a well-greased 9 x 13 pan, place pecans in a layer, then top with a layer of coconut. Prepare cake mix as directed and pour over the coconut.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix well with sugar, syrup, vanilla, salt and butter/margarine.
Pour over 1 cup pecans in pie shell.
(Pecan halves are difficult to cut, though they look good.
I suggest slightly chopped.)
This recipe is generous for pie or 12 tarts. Usually, I use light brown sugar and white syrup or vice versa; all dark makes it too strong.
Baking time is not exact.
Watch it carefully.
Bake at 400° to 375° for no more than 10 minutes to brown the crust.
Then lower to 350° to 325° until done; firm, but not overdone or hard on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 small, uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Mix Pet milk, sugar, margarine and egg yolks well.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Take off heat and add coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: "ding-a-ling penders"
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine peanuts and noodles.
In a 1-quart glass measuring cup, melt butterscotch pieces in microwave oven, 3 minutes at High.
Stir until smooth.
Add to peanut mixture.
Toss gently until coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill to harden.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 2/3 cups.

title: crab canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet and set aside. Combine crab meat, onions, Swiss cheese, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Separate each roll into 3 pieces.
Place on baking sheet.
Spoon crab mixture on top of rolls.
Top with water chestnut.
Bake 12 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: angel's de lite
directions: Gradually
add	sugar
to egg whites.
Fold in vanilla, crushed
crackers and nuts.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Cool and frost.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup (do not add any milk or water).
Mix gelatine with water and stir into soup.
While hot, add other ingredients, shrimp last.
Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks at low speed.
Slowly add juice until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate overnight.

title: "nescafe"(a popular cypriot beverage)
directions: Heat milk slowly.
When it begins to froth, pour into cup with instant coffee and stir (no water).
Sugar may be added, if desired.
Makes 1 cup.

title: crab newberg
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add crab meat and spices and simmer on slow heat for 3 minutes.
Add 2 ounces of sherry and let it reduce by one-half, about 2 minutes, then add cream.
Dilute egg yolks with 1 ounce sherry.
Add and mix carefully.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 people.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered jar.
Dissolve 2 teaspoons tea mix in 1 cup hot water to serve.

title: stollen
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; scald milk; add butter and sugar and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat egg and add to milk mixture with yeast, almond extract and salt.
Stir in 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in almonds, raisins and cherries.
Add remaining flour and mix until smooth.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down; knead lightly and pat to 12-inch circle.
Fold in half; press edges together firmly.
Place on greased sheet (baking).
Brush top with melted butter.
Let rise 1/2 hour in warm place.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Spread top with icing while warm. Makes one large loaf.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix pork and beef together.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Add shrimp and cook 1 more minute. Add beaten eggs and cool. Add mushrooms, carrots, onion, shoyu, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Wrap in lumpia wrappers.
Use only about 1 heaping tablespoonful on a wrapper. Always cool filling before wrapping, otherwise wrapper will fall apart.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and pack first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Beat last 4 ingredients and pour on top of baked crust.
Bake at 350° for an additional 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool before cutting.

title: coconut brunch bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salad oil and flavoring until light and fluffy.
Alternate dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Put into two greased and floured loaf pans or 1 prepared Bundt pan or 6 mini loaf pans.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cook in salt water until tender.
Heat together butter, brown sugar and cloves.
Add carrots.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until glazed.

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Beat all together about 5 minutes.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for
about	1
hour.
Grease
and
flour pan bottom only. When cool, cut cake in 4 layers.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using 1/2 of the cheese in the mixture.
Place in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift salt and baking powder with sifted and measured flour. Blend in shortening.
Combine egg yolk, sugar and milk; stir into flour mixture.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into circles 4 or 5 inches in diameter.
Spread a small amount of fruit filling on half of each round.
Fold the other half of crust over filling.
Seal edges with fork dipped in flour. Fry in deep fat at 360° until browned.
Drain on absorbent paper; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: easy day hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off fat and place meat in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Prepare egg noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Add to casserole dish.
Add soups and mix well.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg and beat well.
Sift together rest of dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Remove all fat from meat and cut 1/4-inch slices along grain. Combine dry and liquid ingredients for marinade.
Marinate meat overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and lay meat strips on oven rack.
Place foil on bottom to catch drips.
Leave oven door ajar and bake at 150° for 6 hours.
Turn oven off and leave meat in another 6 hours.
Yields approximately 1 pound.

title: cherry coffeecake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and butter with electric mixer.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder; mix until smooth.
Place 2/3 of the batter in a greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly.
Place the pie filling evenly over the batter.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoonfuls over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Drizzle with icing made of 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk while warm.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Lay strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: pork chop onion-rice bake
directions: Brown chops in drippings.
Spread rice in bottom of 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of onion soup mix and then sprinkle rest over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid and distribute mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups; pour over rice.
Arrange chops on top of rice and sprinkle reserved onion soup mix on chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove foil and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: brine for fish
directions: Soak 10 hours or overnight. Smoke 8 to 10 hours.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a 9-inch square pan or foil cupcake holders.
Freeze.
Serves 9.

title: awesome appetizers
directions: Mix sugar and ketchup together.
Wrap whole water chestnuts with 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with an uncolored toothpick and place in a baking dish.
Pour sugar-ketchup mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from baking dish and place on serving tray.
Let stand before serving; very hot.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian chiffon cake
directions: Into large mixing bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add in order:
salad oil, egg yolks, pineapple juice and lemon rind.
Beat with spoon until smooth. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl until they hold very stiff peaks.
Slowly pour egg yolks mixture over beaten whites, gently folding until just blended.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into thoroughly clean ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake in preheated slow oven (325°) for 55 minutes, then moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert pan.
Hang until cold. Garnish with whipped cream and drained pineapple (crushed).

title: grandpa o's salad
directions: Mix together and cool.

title: s o s potato pancakes
directions: In top pan of double boiler, melt butter or oleo over medium heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper to melted butter or oleo; stir until smooth over low heat.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened and smooth.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger or ground chuck in skillet with minced onion until well browned.
Drain off grease.
Pour hamburger mixture into white sauce; set aside.

title: 14 layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients and put 4 tablespoons of batter in cake pans. Do not overcook.
Just dry out.

title: chuck wagon roast and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown roast in oil. Place in roaster.
Add flour to meat drippings.
Add buttermilk, water and bouillon.
Cook, stirring until bouillon dissolves (about 10 minutes).
Place carrots and onions around meat.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cook 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables. Cook 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Blend all together except chocolate chips and nuts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips
and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Needs no frosting;
serve
with
ice cream or whipped topping.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook shortening,
onions
and
meat
until
meat
turns color. Add tomatoes,
corn,
chili
and salt.
Add eggs, milk and cornmeal.
Stir into meat.	Cook and stir until thickened. Place in casserole with
ripe olives.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at medium heat.
An
"old faithful" during "the girls" growing up days.

title: banana  cheesecake dessert
directions: Set aside filling and strawberry topping packets from cheesecake mixes.
Place the contents of the crust mix packets in a large bowl; add butter and sugar.
Press into an ungreased 13-inch x 9-inch x 2-inch dish.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the milk and contents of filling packets.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Spread over crust.
Refrigerate for one hour.
Spread contents of strawberry topping over cheesecake.
Top with pineapple and bananas.
Drizzle with chocolate and caramel topping (1/4 cup each).
Spread with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Before serving, drizzle remaining chocolate and caramel toppings. Top with pecans and cherries.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, brown meat and cook onion until done.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice, steak sauce and pepper.
Set aside.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together except cheese.
Place the cheese on top and press down into mixture a little.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Bake covered.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Heat oil, saute onion and garlic.
Add meat and brown.
Blend in tomatoes, taco seasoning and chilies, simmer 10 minutes. Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 chips over bottom of pan.
Spoon in meat mixture the Mozzarella cheese and next sour cream, then top with rest of chips.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: *Set
aside
approximately
1/2 cup flour to dredge the gumdrops, raisins and nuts so that the fruit won't sink to the bottom.
Be sure and add remaining flour to the cake.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with meat tenderizer.
Place roast in baking dish lined with foil.
Pour mushroom soup and water over the roast.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours, or until tender.

title: golden cheddar broccoli bake
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons oleo.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Mix until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils.
Stir constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix in 1/4 cup flakes and corn.
Arrange broccoli in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining 1/2 cup crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter, melted.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix together the butter and powdered sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Roll into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fingers.
Place in oven set at 325° for about 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still slightly warm.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Beat egg yolks, mash cream cheese and add both to hot (not boiling) soup.
Add spinach, beaten egg whites and Parmesan cheese to the above mixture.
Put in large casserole and top with French fried onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
No salt is needed in this recipe because of the use of concentrated soup.
However, if you must use more salt, do it sparingly.
Serves 8.

title: baked fish fillets with wine sauce
directions: In double boiler, saute onion in butter; stir in flour, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and milk.
Cook over boiling water until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Pour Sauterne into 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt; pour on salt.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting 3 times.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble ground beef or pork into 2-quart glass casserole. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once to break up meat.
Add taco seasoning mix and kidney beans.
Microwave on High for 10 to 11 minutes or until flavors are blended, stirring twice.
Let stand about 10 minutes to cool slightly.

title: fluffy cheese omelet
directions: Set oven thermostat at 350°.

title: amish pie crust
directions: Cut flour, salt and lard together.
Stir egg in measuring cup, then
add
enough to measure 2/3 cup of liquid.
Mix liquid into flour mixture.
Chill, then roll.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1/2 cup cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining water to cornstarch to make a smooth paste.
Add paste to sugar mixture.
Cook until transparent. Remove from heat.
Add salt, lemon juice and enough coloring to make a light shade of red.
Reserve 1 cup of berries for garnishing pie.
Cut remaining berries into 2 or 3 pieces.
Pour mixture over cut berries. Let cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream and whole strawberries.

title: gnocchi au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese and butter. Drop dumpling batter in 3/4-inch pieces into boiling water, seasoned with additional tablespoon salt.
Cook gently until dumplings rise to surface.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels. Place in shallow buttered casserole.
Keep hot in preheated 350° oven.
When all dumplings are boiled, pour on butter.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Broil until golden brown. Serve with meat.

title: pop's barbecue sauce
directions: Cover pork roast with water and boil slowly until well done. Cool, then shred into small pieces.
Mix sauce in pan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add meat and continue simmering, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain grease. Add next 8 ingredients and simmer for 25 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Add sugar, flour, margarine, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven. Marshmallows may be added and browned or serve squash with whipped topping.

title: lemon vegetable salad
directions: Mix jello, salt and water.
Cool slightly.
Add mayonnaise, cottage cheese, celery, onion, pimento and green pepper.
Let set until congealed.

title: popular punch
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, lemonade concentrate and cranberry cocktail.
(Chill.)
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 12 (6 ounce) servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add buttermilk all at once and stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Knead 1/2 minute. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Brush with melted fat.
Fold over and cut double biscuits.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Makes 1 cup.
Serve with sour cream for brunch.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over melted butter.
Bake 30 to 40
minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease and flour pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add coconut; stir constantly over low heat until golden brown.
Spread coconut on paper towel to cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese; add milk and sugar alternately, beating well.
Add vanilla; stir in 1 3/4 cups of coconut.
Spread on bottom and top layer and the sides.
Sprinkle top with brown coconut.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal with sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Use a very large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and milk.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Batter will last 6 weeks.
To bake, fill greased tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken almond bake
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Combine chicken, celery, almonds, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 noodles in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add chicken mixture over top of noodles. Then top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the best ever oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
COVER AND LET STAND FOR 1 HOUR.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Blend in egg-raisin mixture; oatmeal, wheat germ and chopped nuts.
Dough will be stiff.
With a tablespoon or cookie scoop, scoop out a ball shape amount.
Put on cookie sheet. Press down just a little to flatten dough a little.
Bake at 350 for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen, depending on the size you make.

title: easy potato rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the potatoes, salt and eggs.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water. Add to creamed mixture. Beat in 2 cups flour and remaining water. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Shape into a ball.
Do not knead.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Divide into thirds. Shape each portion into 15 balls and arrange in three greased 9-inch round baking pans. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 45 rolls.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Cut into wedges.
Melt margarine. In a large pot combine melted margarine and potato wedges.
Cook on low to medium heat for 30 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Mix together flour and onion soup mix.
Add mix to potato wedges and stir.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Turn out onto a baking pan and cook about 25 minutes, uncovered.
Turn wedges once during baking time.
More time may be necessary, depending on how brown and crisp you prefer.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line glass cake pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk and leave set.
Add whipped topping. Pour half of pudding mixture on the crackers in pan.
Add another layer of crackers and pour the rest of the pudding mixture over the crackers, then top with third layer of crackers.
Heat the frosting mix in microwave a minute, then pour over top of crackers, let cool.

title: three beans
directions: Fry bacon; saute onions, green pepper and celery.
Fry hamburg.
Add all 4 cans of beans.
Mix catsup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and brown sugar.
Add this mixture to rest of ingredients.
Mix well and cook for 45 minutes in electric skillet.
Also, may cook in crock-pot or oven.

title: snooker doodle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Dip cookies in above mixture and place on a cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400 for 8 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix well and put 1/2 of mix in Bundt pan.
Put the brown sugar mixture over it.
Add remainder of cake mix.
Take a fork and swirl the mixtures together.
Cook 50 minutes at 325°.

title: punch
directions: May leave out Hawaiian Punch. Mix and chill.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Cut up artichoke hearts into big chunks.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can be used with various breads.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix jello in hot water and 1 cup of pineapple juice.
In separate bowl blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Combine jello with pineapple mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: cheese carrots
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes; melt over hot water.
Cool slightly.
Blend with the cheese, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill just enough to stiffen slightly. Divide into 1/2 teaspoon portions; roll in the grated carrots until well coated.
Place on wax paper and chill.
Stick a sprig in the end of each.

title: morning rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan or spray with Pam. Line pan with frozen rolls.
Sprinkle dry pudding on top of rolls.
In saucepan (or microwave), melt oleo, sugar and cinnamon until dissolved and stir until mixed together.
Pour over rolls.
Add nuts by sprinkling over top.
Cover with foil that has been sprayed with Pam.
Let stand overnight on counter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set in pan 30 minutes, then invert on serving dish.

title: italian meatballs and spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll meatballs and brown in vegetable oil and then place in Italian sauce and simmer for about 3 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for nine minutes.
Add chocolate chips, 1 package at a time and stir each time until dissolved, then add Marshmallow Creme; add vanilla.

title: mustard pickle
directions: Chop peppers and onions fine.
Cook them separate; drain.
Put in kettle with next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil. Mix the last 3 ingredients with water to make paste.
Pour in with other ingredients and boil 5 minutes.
Stir because it will stick quick. Put in jars and seal.
Makes about 10 pints.

title: baked bean surprise
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and bell pepper.
Add pork and beans.
Stir in A.1. sauce and brown sugar.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: green punch
directions: Mix and sweeten Kool-Aid by directions on the package. Add pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Sweeten to taste and chill. Makes 2 to 4 gallons.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and place in baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayo and egg; blend together. Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix and dissolve well the first 3 ingredients.
Add the next 2 and chill.
Mix the sour cream, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Spread over the chilled jello and chill.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Cook vegetables in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except meat.
Stir well.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Combine soup, mayo, eggs, cheese, onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; add broccoli.
Spread in casserole dish (greased with Pam).
Dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb skillet cake
directions: Put rhubarb in a heavy iron skillet or pan with brown sugar. Mix the sugar and oleo; add eggs, soda and sour milk.
Add flour. Pour this over the rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn upside-down so rhubarb is on top.

title: merichka's salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients together and shake well.
Refrigerate. Makes 1 pint.

title: brian's favorite instant hot tea mix
directions: Mix well.
To a cup of hot water, add two or three teaspoons or to taste.
Store tea mixture in an airtight container: jar, plastic or Ziploc baggie.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Grease 18 muffin tin cups. Fill about 1/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 18 Quick and Easy Rolls.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Melt bacon drippings in heavy pot or Dutch oven.
Add sliced onion, shredded cabbage and soup stock.
Cover pot and bring to boil, then simmer for 1/2 hour.
Serve with cornbread.
Pass a cruet of cider vinegar with this cabbage.
Dunk cornbread in the pot likker.
Good.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip with enough pineapple juice to make it thin.
In a medium size bowl, combine apples, pineapple and celery.
Pour in pineapple juice and Miracle Whip and blend well. Put into refrigerator and allow to become cool.
Serve either plain or with lettuce.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring potatoes, water and onion to a boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes for flavor to develop.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Sift together confectioners sugar and cocoa, then add peanut butter and vanilla.
Melt margarine and mix together.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan and refrigerate for 1 hour until set.
Remove from refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: polish cabbage soup
directions: Combine cabbage, tomatoes, puree, water, butter, juice, sugar and salt
in
a
large
kettle.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Beat
egg
yolks
and
sour
cream	in a small bowl. Gradually add 1	cup
of
hot
soup
into
egg mixture.	Stir contents of bowl gradually into soup kettle.
Remove from heat and stir
constantly to prevent eggs from curdling.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs; add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake on bottom shelf of oven at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: zesty bacon dip
directions: In small bowl, combine sour cream, milk, bacon, green onions and horseradish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour to blend flavors. Garnish as desired. Serve with crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: mike's cookies
directions: Mix well first four ingredients.
Add soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° on sprayed cookie sheet.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread chopped pecans and coconut on bottom.
Prepare cake mix.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Mix next 4 ingredients.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes, or until done.
Let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer cooked macaroni alternately with grated cheese in 1-quart ovenproof casserole. Beat eggs with milk; pour over macaroni-cheese mixture. Top with crumbs. Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until custard is set and top is crispy brown. Serves 4.

title: famous pear relish
directions: Grind pears in food processor and drain.
Grind peppers and onions.
Combine all ingredients and boil for 25 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.
Process in water bath canner for 10 minutes. Delicious with dried beans and vegetable soup.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook vegetables (bell pepper, celery, onions and garlic) in broth until tender.
Cook spaghetti and drain (better if cooked in chicken broth).
Mix spaghetti, chicken, cheese, soup, mushrooms and vegetables with broth and remaining ingredients.
Fill buttered casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may freeze dish before cooking.
Does not require covering; if you do cover, remove cover about 10 minutes prior to removing from oven.
This will make 2 casseroles; 1 to eat now and 1 to freeze for later.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix yellow corn meal with cold water, enough to get it stirred together.
Add it to boiling water until well blended.
Stir until well blended with boiling water.
Cook for 2 hours in double boiler.
Pour into oblong pan and slice when cold.
Fry slowly until brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: beef soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in a large saucepan over medium heat until brown, stirring to separate meat.
Drain drippings.

title: flamingo punch
directions: Cook sugar and water (8 cups) in a large pot until all sugar is dissolved; cool.
Strain fruit juice and combine with sugar mixture in large container.
Add water and ice just before serving.
Makes 6 gallons.
May divide recipe by 8, 4 or 2.

title: potato cakes
directions: Cook enough Irish potatoes to make 2 cups mashed potatoes. Mash and add flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended, adding more or less flour and milk.
Drop by patties in hot shortening and fry until golden brown.

title: orange beets
directions: Moisten cornstarch with 1/2 of the water to make a smooth paste; set aside.
Mix the juice, remaining water, vinegar and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling and add the cornstarch mixture.
Stir to prevent lumping, cooking until clear and thickened.
Add butter and beets.
Cook on low until beets are heated through and serve.

title: "never fail" popovers
directions: Break eggs into bowl. Add flour, milk and salt.
Mix well with spoon. Do not smooth out lumps.
Fill greased muffin tin 3/4 full. Put into cold oven set at 450°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Don't open oven during baking and they will "pop up" every time.

title: mazola no-roll pastry shell
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine oil and milk; whip with a fork.
Pour over flour mixture, mixing until flour is completely dampened.
Press evenly and firmly with fingers to line bottom, sides and rim of pan.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: *Substitute for pourable fruit:
3/4 cup no-sugar added strawberry fruit spread and 1/4 cup warm water.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Cream the 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together.
Add pretzels and stir.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: twice baked potato dish
directions: Melt butter; add soup mix.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into slices. Put in baking dish.
Pour butter and soup mix over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle bacon and cheese on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: july salad
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Thoroughly mix in cold water. Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken. Blend in peaches, honeydew, blueberries and grapes, distributing fruit throughout gelatin mixture. Refrigerate several hours or overnight, until firm. Serve on lettuce or other greens.

title: no-cook modeling dough
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Add vegetable oil.
Store in airtight container.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix salt, nutmeg and flour in plastic bag.
Shake chicken in flour mixture.
Brown in shortening in skillet.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Arrange pineapple over chicken.
Blend reserved juice and soy sauce with cornstarch, sugar and celery salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: quiche noel
directions: Line a 9-inch quiche dish or pie pan with pastry; trim excess pastry around edges.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer; let cool on rack.

title: the red heads brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter with chocolate over lowest heat setting, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then flour, then nuts.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until top is dull and barely set.
Cool in pan on rack to room temperature, then cut into squares.

title: catalina salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and tomatoes.
Add any other salad fixings you wish (cucumbers, peppers, etc.).
Cut onion in large pieces.
Add 1/2 can kidney beans and/or 1/2 can Great Northern beans, rinsed. Add dressing and mix.
Before serving, add olives and Fritos.

title: chicken ole
directions: Combine taco sauce, mustard and lime juice in large bowl.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator at least 30 minutes.
Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat until foamy.
Remove chicken; reserve marinade.
Add chicken to skillet; cook about 10 minutes or until brown on both sides. Add marinade; cook about 5 minutes or until chicken is tender and marinade glazes chicken.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Boil marinade over high heat 1 minute.
Pour over chicken.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with sour cream.

title: my aunt's large crock spiced pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers.
Mix all ingredients above together. Put enough cucumbers into mixture so that they are about 2 inches below the liquid.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, vinegar, oil, orange juice and salt.
Marinate overnight.
After marinated, combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.

title: hungarian goulash with noodles
directions: Brown meat on all sides in heavy frypan or Dutch oven.
Add onions.
Combine mustard, paprika, brown sugar and salt.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and ketchup and add to mustard mixture.
Add to meat.
Add 1 cup of the water; stir.
Cover. Cook over low heat 2 1/2 hours or until meat is very tender. Blend flour with remaining 1/2 cup of water; add to meat mixture. Stir until thickened.
Boil noodles in salted water until tender. Drain.
Serve mixture over noodles.
Serves 8.

title: veggie salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Mix all of the ingredients together; put in refrigerator.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Mix as listed. Let stand overnight in an airtight container.

title: glaze
directions: Mix and use.
Can be stored in sealed container.

title: chicken legs
directions: Layer in a large baking dish: chicken, onion, green pepper, tomatoes, and tomato sauce.
Then pour in soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil and water.
Beat well.
Add mix, gelatin, flour and crushed strawberries.
Pour into rectangle pan, Pammed and floured.
Bake according to package directions.
When cool, frost with following.

title: pulled molasses candy
directions: Boil molasses and vinegar to hard ball stage.
Add butter and soda and let boil to crack stage.
Pour into a buttered pan. When cool enough to handle, pull until light and porous, using tips of fingers and thumbs.
Cut into a small piece, using scissors and place on buttered plate to cool.

title: sweet potato-pumpkin puddings
directions: Combine dates and water.
Blend sugars, egg and butter.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts and cooled date mixture.
Pour into 11 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with brown-sugar sauce.
(Combine 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter or margarine and 1 1/2 cups boiling water.) Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 40 minutes.
Cut in squares; invert on plates.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.
Use 1/2 cup more water for more pudding.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix first two ingredients.
Beat well and soak fish in it for 15 minutes.

title: liver and onions
directions: Roll slices of liver in flour. Saute in butter until brown on both sides. Saute thinly sliced onion rings in another frying pan until golden brown.
Place liver on platter.
Turn onion rings into pan in which liver was cooked.
Add 2 tablespoons hot water. Stir to loosen sediment in pan.
Mix.
Pour over liver and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes; drain well.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add mayonnaise, pepper and cheese.
Spoon into ungreased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown (20 to 30 minutes).
Serve hot with crackers or toasted pieces of Italian bread.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together the brown sugar, molasses, Crisco and egg.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix together.
Roll in ball and sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They will appear not to be done.
Makes soft cookies.

title: easy muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan.
Mix all ingredients together; fill muffin pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: dietetic spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is gone (cool).
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Beat well, sift dry ingredients together.
Add to other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in loaf or tube pan sprayed with Pam (or use grease) at 350° for 1 hour.
(It cooks in my oven in about 30 minutes.)

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Dip fruit chunks and enjoy.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Chill at least 2 hours. Serve with slice of lemon, if desired.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins.
Beat egg with a fork; stir in milk and oil.
Blend dry ingredients and mix with liquid just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy. Add blueberries.
Mix lightly, but do not overmix.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 9 medium or 12 small.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries and chopped nuts; let jell.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Dream Whip that has been whipped as directed on package.
Put on top of Jell-O.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
You may use any type berry with Jell-O in that flavor.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add berries with sugar and stir well.
Stir in pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of this mixture into 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.
Let set in refrigerator until firm, then spread with sour cream.
Cover the sour cream with the remaining gelatin mixture.
Do not refrigerate the last half of the gelatin mixture until you pour it over the sour cream. Chill until set and serve.

title: frankfurter pate
directions: Advance preparation:
Place first 8 ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend smooth, stopping to scrape sides often.
Chill mixture in small mold or bowl until firm.

title: black forest pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add margarine and milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add small amount of mixture to eggs.
Return mixture to pan.
Fold 1/2 can cherry filling.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is set.
Cool and chill for 1 hour.
Combine topping with chocolate.
Spread on top of pie. Place remaining cherries on top of pie around edge.

title: french coffee cake
directions: Knead dough gently until smooth.
Roll dough to measure 12 x 18-inches.
Spread soft butter over 2/3 of dough.
Turn 6-inches of unbuttered dough over and then other 6. Put in cookie sheet with wax paper and cover with towel.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then take dough out and cut in half, then roll out 8 x 14-inches.
Put about 1/2 cup filling in center of dough.
Put on lightly greased sheet, cut or leave plain.
Put in refrigerator for about 20 minutes, then bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Then butter over the top.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and salt in large bowl.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Combine green pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed in a large pan and bring to boil.
Add tomatoes and onions and bring to boil again.
Pack pickles into hot jars; cover with boiling vinegar mixture.
Place hot lids on jars immediately. Makes 3 pints.

title: chinese soyameat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with potato chips, dry Chinese noodles or croutons.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in deep dish or less time in shallow dish.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix everything but vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar. Top pie with meringue.
Brown meringue.

title: creamy caramel dip
directions: Stir together caramels and half and half in a 4-cup glass measure. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until dip is smooth, stirring every minute.
Serve warm or at room temperature with fresh fruit, round cake
or angel food cake cubes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Skin breasts and pat dry.
Dip in melted butter, then dip in dry ingredients.
Pour enough butter in a baking dish to cover bottom.
Place chicken in and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into log and roll into nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers or small toast triangles.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix in butter.
Add cheese to macaroni. Heat milk.
Mix in eggs; stir into macaroni.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's eggs and potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until almost tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside. In heavy 10-inch skillet, saute bacon until crisp and drain on paper towel.
Reserve drippings.
In 3 tablespoons drippings, saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add potatoes, 1/3 at a time and saute until lightly browned.
Remove from pan as they are browned.
Saute 1/3 more until they are all browned, making sure that they lie flat.
Return potatoes to skillet.
Add more drippings, if needed.
Keep heat low.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper until well blended but not foamy.
Pour egg mixture over potatoes.
Slowly and evenly sprinkle with bacon bits.
Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are set, about 5 to 6 minutes. Taste for seasoning and serve from skillet.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Mix first five ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.
Make into shape of strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Insert a slivered almond as the stem.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Cream together. Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Mix together. Add Wheaties and pecans, folding in. Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° until brown about 10 minutes.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Mix well.
Then add flour and cinnamon.
Knead if necessary.
Pat down on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fingers.
Brush with the egg white mixed with a little water.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: tomato soup dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Place in glass jar.
Makes 1 quart.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Put peaches into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: new orleans dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill. Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: yams with oranges
directions: Arrange half of yam slices in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with half the orange slices, 2 tablespoons brown sugar and some nuts and spices.
Then repeat layers.
Garnish with additional orange slices.
Combine juice and margarine; pour over all.
Bake at 325° about 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: touchdown taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread refried beans over bottom of 9 x 9 baker pan.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Press garlic into bowl with creamy mixture and mix well.
Spread over beans.
Shred cheese over the top and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Chop olives, Snip Cilantro.
Sprinkle chopped tomato, onions, olives and cilantro over hot dip.
Garnish with additional sour cream if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked rice
directions: Brown rice in oleo; add chopped onion and green pepper.
Put in 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add 1 to 2 cups water.
As it cooks, if too dry, add more water.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll thin; cut and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll in 3/4 cup chopped nuts.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cocoa in bowl.
Stir in evaporated milk, vanilla, eggs and butter.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Place in pie shells and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool on racks.

title: don's chili
directions: Combine ground beef and onions in a covered skillet; add pepper and cook until the redness is gone.
Add the chili powder and about 1 cup water.
Add some salt to the cooking meat and simmer 15 or 20 minutes.
In a separate 5 to 6-quart pot, combine the V-8 juice, tomato soup, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, garlic powder, 1 to 2 cups water (for desired consistency), sugar and beans.
Mix thoroughly and heat to near boiling.
Add the cooked meat and onions.
Bring to a boil and add the spaghetti (broken into 2-inch pieces) and cook until spaghetti is tender.
Add more salt, sugar or water as you wish.
Skim fat from chili and serve immediately or later.
Sometimes chili is even better the second day!

title: lemon curd tarts
directions: In the top of a double boiler, combine the lemon juice, lemon rind and sugar.
Add the butter and heat over boiling water until the butter is melted, stirring occasionally.
Now stir in the eggs and continue cooking, stirring constantly until the mixture is thick enough to pile slightly (about 15 minutes).
Cool thoroughly, then chill.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Slice stems from bell peppers and scoop out seeds, etc. Add salt
and
pepper
to insides, to taste.
Put peppers into boiling water for 2 to 4 minutes and drain well.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray; add margarine.
Place over medium heat until margarine melts.
Add onion, celery and bacon; saute until vegetables are tender and bacon is browned. Drain clams, reserving juice; set clams aside.
Add reserved clam juice, broth and potato to pan.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until potato is tender.
Combine flour and 1 1/2 cups milk; stir until smooth.
Add flour mixture, remaining 2 1/2 cups milk, clams, pepper and hot sauce to potato mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes or until mixture is thickened (do not boil).

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with Pam.
Mix ingredients and add butter to top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: tomato dressing(salt free, oil free, low-cal)
directions: Put all the ingredients into a small jar, with a tightly fitting lid.
Seal the jar and shake well to mix ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hour to allow dressing to thicken.
Excellent on simple green salads.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in baking mix and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter dipped in baking mix. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zesty picante bake
directions: Grease pan (10 x 1 1/2-inch). Mix Bisquick, water, beans and add meat, then sauce, then cheese. Spread in pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Add 2 cans water with the soup and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese to top of casserole and bake for 15 minutes.
Total cooking time 1 hour.

title: midwest squares
