directions: On greased cookie sheet, pat dough into a rectangle about 10 x 13-inches and about 1/4-inch thick.
Press crushed cereal on top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares or diamond shapes.

title: nut horns
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Mix yeast with 1/4 cup warm water, then add sugar and small amount of sour cream to ferment.
Add oleo to salt and flour in a large bowl and mix until crumbly.
Add egg yolks, yeast mixture and remainder of sour cream; mix well.
Form into ball; turn out on board sprinkled lightly with flour.
Knead until smooth, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill at least 3 hours or overnight. On board sprinkle with sugar, roll each part into a 12-inch circle. Cut into 12 triangles.
Spread with Walnut Filling.
Roll up and bake until golden brown at 350°, about 25 minutes.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar (optional).
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding pecans last.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 400° (hot) oven 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Outer edges of filling should be set, center slightly soft.

title: brownies(low-fat, low cholesterol)
directions: Mix the applesauce and the sugar. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make meatballs and put them in the oven until brown at approximately 350°.
Put oil in a frying pan and deep fry onion and peppers.
Put meatballs in a big pan and mix all the ingredients together.
Mix cornstarch and 1/2 cup water and cook in pan until thick.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Stir together all ingredients and put into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let set for a few minutes.

title: good old southern-style tasty meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine and mix well all ingredients for meat loaf except bread; then, saturate each slice of bread with water, squeeze water out and add to mixture in bowl, crumbling wet bread as you do so.
Mix all well again.
Pour this mixture into a meat loaf pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Take out and loosely cover with tin foil for about 30 minutes before slicing. (It seems to slice better and not fall apart this way.)

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp.
Add onions and saute for a couple of minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over lettuce and turn pot over lettuce to wilt.
Serve immediately.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into desired shapes and sizes. Add sugar, water and margarine. Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done and syrup is thick.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan coated with nonstick spray or margarine and floured.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts for toasted effect instead of icing.
Nuts inside are optional.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: pig pick'n cake
directions: Cake: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges. Divide into 3 equal layers. Bake at 350° for 22 minutes. Cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and place in casserole.

title: caramel pecan pie(from watkinsville garden club cookbook)
directions: Place 1 cup nuts in bottom of pastry shell and cover with half of caramel topping.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each.
Pour over topping.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes; cool.
Garnish with additional 1/2 topping, drizzled over top and additional nuts.

title: glazed carrots and pineapple
directions: Cook carrots with salt and water, covered, until barely tender.
Drain any remaining liquid into measuring cup, then add pineapple syrup to measure 1 cup in all.
Mix with cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear. Stir in butter.
Add carrots and pineapple tidbits.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt butter; stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa; beat until well blended.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies just begin to pull away from sides.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes about 36 brownies.

title: light whole wheat biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir together the first 4 ingredients. Add milk to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: aunt grace's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix boiled eggs, chicken, pepper to taste, and enough broth to make soupy.
Pour over crumbled cornbread.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: "potato soup"
directions: Cook diced potatoes and bay leaves in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and vinegar; stir well.
Remove from heat, add gravy mixture and mix well.
Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Saute onions in a little shortening and stir into soup.

title: tangy chicken
directions: Mix ingredients; marinate chicken for one hour.
Put in broiler for 10 minutes or so.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut cucumbers thin, place in a bowl and cover with water and 1/4 cup salt.
Drain, add sliced onion and sprinkle 1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar.
Let stand until liquid forms (about 1 hour).
Add vinegar to cover cukes, season with salt and pepper.
Chill and serve.

title: window cleaner
directions: Place 1 frozen T.V. Dinner in oven and bake 35 minutes.
Take shower, read paper and remove dinner after timer goes off. Grouse, carp and whine either before, during or after your meal. But remember, you really haven't got it that bad after all.
Who made sure that it was in the freezer!

title: baby rough's rosemary muffins
directions: Simmer milk, raisins and rosemary in pan.
Remove from heat, add butter to melt.
Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Beat egg into the cooled milk mixture.
Add to the dry ingredients, mix slightly until dry ingredients are moist.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, 1/3 full, then put 3/4-inch cube cream cheese in the center.
Cover with remaining mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Mash corn flakes to be topped over mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Have prepared 1 unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Mix sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and pie spice together with a fork.
Add eggs, beating well, then add milk.
Mix, then add pumpkin.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until a knife blade inserted in the center of pie filling comes out clean.
Cool before cutting.

title: fruited chiffon squares
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes; stir 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove unmelted ice.
Fold 1 cup Cool Whip into 1/2 of gelatin until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill for about 5 minutes, until set.
Add fruit to remaining gelatin and spoon over creamy layer.
Chill until firm.

title: apricot bars
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, egg, flour, salt and coconut.
Mix well.
Spread three quarters of this mixture on greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread apricot preserves on top. Combine remaining 1/4 mixture with chopped nuts and crumble on top. Pat to spread evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown on top.
Cut into bars when warm.

title: friendship cake
directions: Keep in large nonmetallic bowl and wrap loosely with Saran Wrap.

title: italian chops and rice
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper to taste.
Brown on both sides in oil in a large ovenproof skillet.
Remove chops and set aside.
Add onion and green pepper and saute until tender-crisp. Stir in tomatoes, broth, seasonings and rice.
Bring to a boil. Arrange chops on top.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Fluff rice with fork.
Makes 6 servings with 409 calories per serving.

title: skillet herb roasted chicken
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Coat chicken with flour, sage and thyme.
Cook chicken in margarine 10 minutes.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Mix saltines with milk and other ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour; fry until done.
Mix onions, celery, green peppers, 1 can tomato soup and 1/2 can water.
Simmer for 1 hour or until gravy is thick.

title: peach ice cream
directions: In heavy pan, heat milk on low until hot, but not boiling. Stir in sugar and salt until dissolved. Gradually stir about a quarter of the hot mixture into the beaten eggs, mixing constantly.
Return all to the saucepan, stirring constantly. Continue to cook and stir for 10 to 12 minutes or until mixture coats the back of a metal spoon.
Remove from heat and cool. Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight.
In a large bowl, combine the cream, fruit, vanilla and almond extract.
Add the chilled milk mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a chilled freezer can of a 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: kale and red peppers
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine oil, red peppers, garlic and chili pepper.
Saute over medium heat for 2 or 3 minutes, stirring until peppers are tender.
Stir in chicken broth and kale, mustard or turnip greens.
Bring to a boil, then toss greens in pan and cover with liquid.
Reduce heat to medium and cook 25 minutes or until greens are tender.
Serves 4. Contains 0 cholesterol and 2 grams fat.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large bowl that will allow it to be stirred.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, melt butter, then stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Allow it to boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour mixture over popped corn.
Mix well.

title: corn bake
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in sprayed casserole at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil until well blended, then add dry ingredients.
Mix again until well blended.
Add zucchini, nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5 x 4-inch) bread pans or 3 smaller pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: awesome stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells like lasagna or spaghetti noodles and coat lightly with olive oil.
Drain and save.
Fry ground beef (or sausage and beef) with 1 green onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cool and drain.
Mix beef mixture with cottage cheese, 1 green onion, salt, pepper and cayenne pepper to taste and egg.
Stuff into shells.
Then pour 1/2 jar or can of your favorite marinara sauce or spaghetti sauce into glass casserole dish.
Set in shells and proceed to cover with sauce.
Top with grated Cheddar and bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, flour, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans
in
1/4 cup butter in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir frequently. Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Cream 1 cup butter;
gradually add sugar, creaming well. Blend
in eggs;
beat
well	after each.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after
each
addition.
Stir
in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups pecans. Turn
into	3
(9-inch)
round
layer pans, greased and floured on bottom.
Bake
at
for
to 30 minutes.
Butter Pecan Frosting should be under cake.

title: congealed strawberry-buttermilk salad
directions: In a large saucepan, mix jello and pineapple until jello is dissolved.
Set aside and let cool, then add buttermilk, nuts, Cool Whip and fruit.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: golden chili chicken
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat with hot oil, cook the chicken until it is brown.
Drain the excess fat.
Add all other ingredients to the chicken.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: white star peanut clusters
directions: Melt together the candy stars and wax over hot water.
Mix all together and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: carrot soup
directions: In a 2-quart microwave proof casserole, combine the garlic, onion, orange juice, carrots and potatoes.
Cover tightly; cook on High for 7 minutes or until tender, stirring only once.
Puree in food processor or blender; pour the cream into the bowl of processor and continue processing until smooth.
Return to casserole dish; add broth, black pepper, cayenne, nutmeg and chives.
Stir well and chill for at least 1 hour or up to 4 days. To serve, divide soup among 4 bowls.
Arrange 3 pieces of chive tops on top of each bowl of soup.
Serve.

title: mom's 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Add shrimp. Chill.
Serve with chips.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Combine rhubarb with sugar, margarine and flour.
Mix well. Beat egg yolks and add.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and fold in. Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and 45 more minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix raisins, fruit and nuts with flour mixture.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with hot applesauce.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Crush graham and saltine crackers together.
Add butter and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Mixt together pudding and milk.
Add softened ice cream.
Pour over crumb crust. Chill.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Butterfingers.
Can be frozen or keeps well in refrigerator.

title: baked corn
directions: Take 10 to 12 crushed saltine crackers, not fine, but in chunks (about 2 handfuls).
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix until cracker crumbs are moist but not dissolved.
It will look sloppy. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until set and slightly brown on edges and middle doesn't jiggle.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition. Add nuts and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, vanilla, red food coloring and water.
Sift together in separate bowl cocoa, salt and flour. Add to mix alternately with buttermilk.
Mix vinegar with soda; then fold into batter.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt the
butter;
stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Stir constantly until
mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes without
stirring.
Remove
from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Slowly
pour
mixture
over
popped corn and mix well. Turn into shallow baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 250° oven,
stirring
every 15 minutes.
After cooling, break into small chunks or into individual kernels.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and roll 1/8-inch thick rolls (as for butterhorn rolls).
Roll around a date.
Makes 80 to 100.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
(I use chicken broth instead of water.)
Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Mix well.
Fold in diced chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until it bubbles.
This freezes well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: granny black's ham pasties
directions: Mix softened margarine and softened cream cheese together. Add flour and ice water to make dough.
Cover and chill overnight. When ready to make pastry, mix remaining ingredients to a spreading consistency for filling.
Break off dough, one piece at a time, large enough to make one pastry.
Roll out thin in a circle, about 2 inches in diameter.
Scoop filling on top and fold over into half moon and seal pastry.
Bake at 400° until brown. Great for parties.
Freezes very well.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans thoroughly and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: crunchy caramel snack mix
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Set aside.
Cook sugar, margarine and syrup over medium heat until mixture comes to boil. Cook without stirring 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and cream of tartar, then vanilla.
Pour syrup over cereals until coated.
Bake at 170° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 10 cups.

title: potato-bean soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, onion and celery in large pot; cover with water.
Add bay leaf and salt.
Bring to boil; simmer gently for 30 minutes. Add beans, ketchup, dill and parsley.
Continue simmering.

title: pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, Cool Whip, crushed pineapple with juice, cream pudding and coconut.
Add marshmallows.
Mix altogether.

title: old-fashioned cracked sugar cookies
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy.
Add sugars, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, beating well.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet and remove to rack to cool completely.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: oriental chicken soup
directions: Simmer all but vinegar together until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add vinegar.

title: fudge
directions: Leave cheese out of refrigerator 24 hours.
Mix all the ingredients with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together over hot water; cool. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light; add sugar and chocolate mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Put into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana delight
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine.
Mix in flour, sugar and nuts.
Press into pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Stir in bananas, vanilla and cinnamon.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat until blended.
Stir in chips and walnuts. Spoon batter into loaf pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Shield with foil after 1 hour.
Test with toothpick until comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and the pudding mix.
Beat slowly with eggbeater or mixer on low setting until well mixed.
(Do not overbeat.)
Pour at once into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs lightly over top.
Chill about one hour.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Place all ingredients in a large crock-pot.
Simmer on high until butter and candy are completely melted.
Keep hot.
Serve from crock-pot.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix together and pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: five flavored pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add extracts.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy and add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour with dry ingredients; add beaten egg, melted shortening and orange juice.
Combine only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in nuts, cranberries and orange rind.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brush uncooked chicken with butter, salt and pepper to taste. Mix rice with all other ingredients and place in large pan.
Put chicken on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: saturday salmon supper
directions: Saute onion in the margarine until golden.
Blend in flour. Gradually add soup and milk, stirring.
Boil 1 minute.
Add flaked, boned salmon.
Drop Bisquick dumplings by teaspoons on top after you've put salmon mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: ham rolls
directions: Split rolls lengthwise.
Mix last 5 ingredients.
Spread mixture on rolls.
Layer ham and Swiss cheese.
Replace top half of roll.
Cut each roll.
Heat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat egg white stiff. Set aside. Scald cream.
Set aside and cool.
Cream the Crisco and butter. Add sugar and vanilla and beat.
Add egg white and beat. Add cream and beat until smooth.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased loaf pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Place potatoes and enough water to cover in a saucepan and cook until tender.
Cool slightly and peel.
In a large bowl, mash potatoes.
Stir in butter, sugar and raisins.
Place in a 2 qt. baking dish, and sprinkle with nuts and marshmallows.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or heated through and marshmallows brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: winnie pooh potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion.
Mix in eggs, flour, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Pour as thin as a pancake and fry in a little oil on a grill until brown.

title: chicken boursin bundles
directions: Combine Boursin cheese, chicken, onion, milk, salt and pepper and mix well. Roll the puff pastry into 1 large square and cut into 4 squares. Spoon 1/4 of chicken mixture into the center of each pastry square. Bring the 4 corners together in the center, pinching seams to seal. Beat the egg with water in a small bowl. Brush the top of each pastry bundle. Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top of each bundle and arrange on a baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. May be prepared ahead and chilled or frozen to enjoy later.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add 3 cans milk and 1 glass lemon juice. Makes 3 pies.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add beans and soup.
Cook 10 minutes.
Make chili powder, flour, water and salt into a paste.
Blend into meat mixture.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add margarine, sugar, eggs, etc.
Stir in half the chocolate chips. Spread the other half on top after cake is baked.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in jelly roll pan or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: rugalach
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Blend with hands and roll into 2 balls.
Wrap balls and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, combine sugar, cinnamon, and walnuts.
Set aside.
Roll out each dough ball to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place dinner plate over dough and cut into large circle, using plate as a guide.
Slice each circle into 8 pie slices.
Place tablespoon of cinnamon-sugar mixture on large end of pie slice and roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy moon bread
directions: Generously grease a loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine warm water with yeast (from hot roll mix).
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in egg, butter and seasonings.
Add flour and mix; stir in olives and cheese.
Cover; let rise until doubled in size.
Knead dough 10 strokes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put cheese ball in refrigerator to chill, then roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven and prepare and bake brownies according to package directions; let cool.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break candy bars into small pieces.
Break brownies into small pieces and place half of them in the bottom of a large glass bowl or trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse, half the candy and half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients, sprinkling second layer of whipped topping with crushed candy.
You may use pecans instead.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix other ingredients with margarine.
Pour in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jewell's rocks (christmas cookie)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture; mix lightly.
Fold in raisins, nuts and some red cut up candied cherries.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; add juices and mashed bananas.
Mix everything except carbonated beverage.
Divide into 6 equal portions in 6 freezer cartons and freeze ahead of time.
Take out about 2 hours before serving time.
Mix 1 portion with one bottle of carbonated beverage (lemon-lime soda or ginger ale).
Makes about 72 punch cup servings of slushy-type punch.
No extra ice is needed.

title: almond bars
directions: Beat together the sugar and eggs until thick and light.
Add the margarine, flour, almond extract and dash of salt.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork, with a little flour, so mix won't stick.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until brown.

title: golden peachy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in single layer in shallow roasting pan.
Combine peach syrup with lemon juice, soy sauce and mashed peach halves.
Pour over chicken; dot with margarine.
Bake at 375°; baste often until chicken is done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Place 8 canned peach halves around chicken 15 minutes before chicken is done.

title: crisco pie crust
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add water 1/2 at time and mix just until it goes together into dough.
Do not knead.
Roll out on floured board.
Make 1 pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add vanilla and buttermilk. Mix thoroughly.
Beat in melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Put thawed spinach in skillet.
Add garlic and 2 tablespoons oil.
Coat well.
Saute 2 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend well with mixer until creamy.
Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients togther. Bake at 350 for 35 - 45 minutes.

title: windex mixture
directions: *Cut 1 roll in half.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients to form paste, then add dry ingredients and then vinegar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Split two round pans into 4 layers.

title: chutney glazed cheese pate
directions: In a bowl,
beat
together
cheeses,
curry powder, dry sherry and salt.
Spread
mixture	1/2-inch thick on a serving dish. Cover and
chill
until
firm.
At serving time, spread top with chutney and sprinkle with finely chopped green onion. Serve with bland crackers.
Serves 18.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Form into balls and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup mix, water and tomato sauce and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover. Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: bisquick mixture
directions: Mix
to
cornmeal consistency.	Store in covered can or bowl and store at room temperature.

title: baked apples
directions: Cut corn from cob and
scrape
cob.
Put
in heavy pan. Add some bacon grease and a small chunk of butter.
Add enough water to keep from sticking.
Bring
corn
to
a	boil and add salt and sugar to taste.
Cook down to desired consistency.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, flour, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla in a large bowl.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: hot cheese
directions: Put cream cheese, Velveeta and pecans in mixing bowl.
Place 2 squares of waxed paper on table, flat.
Sprinkle paprika heavily on wax paper (all over).
With your hands, thoroughly mix the cheese and pecans until thoroughly blended.
Dash in the Tabasco sauce (about 1/2 bottle) and mix well.

title: classic blueberry pie
directions: For filling, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in water and add 3 cups blueberries.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture thickens and begins to boil. Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Place remaining 2 cups blueberries in pie pan lined with pastry.
Stir butter and lemon juice into cooked berry mixture.
Spoon over fresh berries in crust.
Cover pie with gashed top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: To 3 cups of whole large hulled berries, add 1/2 cup sugar. Let stand 1 hour.
Cut remaining berries in pieces.
Put in a small saucepan and add 3/4 cup of water.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes. Combine the cornstarch and 1 cup sugar.
Mix well. Add to simmering berries. Cook until mixture is thick and clear, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and 3 drops red food coloring.
Cool. Stand whole berries, cut side down, in pie crust.
Cover with cooled sauce. Chill thoroughly. Decorate with border of sweetened whipped cream.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk together with electric mixer about 2 minutes. Fold Cool Whip into pudding mixture. Set aside.
Line bottom of pan with whole graham crackers.
Put a layer of pudding mixture on top, then repeat layering. Finish with layer of crackers on top.
Ice with chocolate icing and refrigerate.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In saucepan mix soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder, pepper, broccoli and carrots.
Heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Add macaroni and chicken.
Heat through.

title: mandarin orange pie #1
directions: Mix Eagle
Brand
milk	and ReaLemon juice until thick. Blend in Cool
Whip.
Cut
mandarin orange slices into chunks; mix in with
rest	of ingredients.
Add pecans if wanted.	Put in pie shell and chill before serving.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy chili verde
directions: 1. Pierce roast with garlic. Put as much or as little as you want. Sprinkle lightly w/ cumin and lemon pepper.
2. Slow cook roast in oven until done. I cook it at 250°.
Check temp with a meat thermometer. Takes appx 6-8 hrs
to cook.
3. When done trim fat and shread meat into crockpot. Add
remaining ingredients and cook in crockpot several hrs.
As with American chili there are many variables. You
can make this as hot or as mild as you want depending
on heat of salsa and green chilies.
4. If your Chili Verde is too thick add more chicken broth
and if too thin add cornstarch and water mixture.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Brown in margarine.
Add onion, soup and a soup can of water.
Cook slowly until tender, 1 to 2 hours.
Add water as necessary.
Add sour cream and heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: john mozetti
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of oil in skillet and brown ground beef. Cook with onions and pepper until done.
Drain part of grease off. Add 1/2 of both cheeses and all other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with balance of cheese.
Heat in oven about 45 minutes at 375° before serving.
Serves 6 big appetites.

title: taco mountain
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together, set aside.
Spread beans in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with sour cream mixture, followed by a layer of each: guacamole, lettuce, tomato and olives.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Serve cold with tortilla chips for dippers.

title: health bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 large empty fruit cans (tin cans).
Grease well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good to eat with cream cheese.

title: italian flank steak
directions: Pound flank steak and season with salt, pepper and crushed garlic.
Evenly spread bread crumbs and mushrooms over the steak. Roll the steak with seasonings toward the center and secure with string or toothpicks.
Place the steak in a medium or large pot and completely cover with the spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: "pumpkin" punch
directions: Combine sugar and spices; add 1 cup cider and heat until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining cider and orange juice concentrate. Chill.

title: art's spaghetti sauce
directions: Take onion, carrots, celery, green pepper and put into blender to liquify.
Heat olive oil in large pot.
Brown garlic in oil and then discard garlic.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and 16 ounces of water and contents of blender.
Add spices and simmer 3 hours.
Serve on spaghetti.
(Italian sausage, hamburger or lean pork can be added, but cook in another pot first to get rid of excess grease.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks; beat whites until stiff.
Fold yolks into whites. Fold in oil and let mixture set while you mix dry ingredients.

title: hot chocolate for the family
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in airtight container. Add 1/4 cup of mixture to a cup of boiling water for each serving.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and place into an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: banana layer cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add, alternating with flour.
Beat egg whites; fold in.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Combine cake mix and oleo.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to the reserved topping and mix well.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: super chicken
directions: In a large nonstick casserole, combine rice, chicken bouillon and mushrooms.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over top.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Saute chicken breast in butter.
Add cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Stir in chopped mushrooms and jalapeno peppers to taste.

title: parmesan pillows
directions: Prepare biscuit mix as directed on package for rolled biscuits on lightly floured surface.
Knead dough 10 times.
Roll 10 x 6-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Cut each square in half diagonally.
Dip into margarine.
Coat with Parmesan cheese. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, jello and cornstarch together.
Cook until clear, then boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over quartered berries in baked crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in small amount of oil until onion is clear, then mix all ingredients together (reserve 1 cup stuffing crumbs and enough cheese for top).
Pour into casserole dish.
Put cheese on first and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat very well. Add bananas, soda and water mixture, vanilla and lemon juice. Add all dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add nuts.
Bake slowly for about 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: potato rags
directions: Shred potatoes and drop into deep fryer until crispy. Let them drain on paper towels to soak up oil.

title: blueberry sponge cake roll
directions: Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 1 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line bottom with waxed paper and grease again; set aside.

title: hot german bean salad
directions: Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick coating.
Heat skillet over medium-high heat.
In a hot skillet, stir-fry carrot, onion and celery for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: butternut souffle
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Put into a greased baking dish.

title: creamy orange tapioca
directions: Combine all but vanilla in saucepan and let stand 5 minutes. Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Let cool, then cover and refrigerate until chilled and firm.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 109 calories each and .2 g. fat.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks.
Add all the ingredients, except the egg whites, beating well.
Beat the egg whites and fold into the first mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven a little lower and bake until light brown.

title: wet and good chocolate cake
directions: Stir together the oatmeal and boiling water and let sit for 10 minutes.
Reserve 1/2 of the chocolate chips for the top of the cake.
Add the rest of the chips and all of the remaining ingredients to the oatmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Pour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread 1/2 of the chocolate chips on top of cake.
Bake at 350° until done, or approximately 35 minutes.

title: french toast(low cholesterol)
directions: Whisk the first 5 ingredients together in bowl until well beaten.
Soak bread in milk mixture on both sides.
Fry in nonstick pan or griddle until lightly browned on both sides, but still moist inside.
Serve with maple syrup, orange marmalade or powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, pumpkin and egg in mixer until creamy. Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Stir all ingredients and chill.

title: black bean soup-cuban style(frijoles negros)
directions: Wash and rinse beans carefully, selecting out damaged beans (chipped or broken).
Soak beans two hours before cooking.
(Do not drain this water which may become discolored, use it for cooking the beans.)
Poke green pepper with a fork and roast lightly over flame or heat, enough to peel off its skin.
Remove its seeds and discard.

title: holiday trash
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in oven in large pan (bottom of roaster works great!).
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix until coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
